min]] \u2013 sports announcer for [[ESPN]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theathletic.com/291867/2018/03/29/espns-adam-amin-hoping-his-first-womens-final-four-assignment-leads-to-many-more/|title=Less than a month after losing his father, ESPN's Adam Amin makes Women's Final Four debut|last=Deitsch|first=Richard|website=The Athletic|date=March 29, 2018|accessdate=May 12, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mr. Capone-E|Fahad Azam]] \u2013 stage name Mr. Capone-E [[Sureno]] rapper; born in [[Karachi, Pakistan]]; immigrated to San Gabriel Valley in Los Angeles\n*[[Fareed Haque]] \u2013 guitarist of Pakistani and Chilean descent<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fareed.com/bio.html |title=bio |publisher=Fareed.com |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Aishah Hasnie]] \u2013 television reporter and news anchor for [[Fox news]]<ref>{{Cite news|first= |last= |authorlink=   |title=Aishah Hasnie anchors FOX59\u2032s First at Four and is a FOX59 Investigates reporter.   |newspaper=[[WXIN|FOX 59]] |date= |url=https://fox59.com/author/aishahhasniefox59/  |accessdate=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Christel Khalil]] \u2013 of mixed Pakistani and African American descent; played Lily Winters on the [[CBS]] soap opera ''[[The Young and the Restless]]''\n*[[Amir Khan (boxer)|Faryal Makhdoom Khan]] \u2013 Media personality and wife of [[British-Pakistani]] boxer [[Amir Khan (boxer)|Amir Khan]].\n*[[Aamina Sheikh]] \u2013 actress and model best known for portraying the main leads in films ''[[Seedlings (film)|Seedlings]]'', ''[[Armaan (2013 film)|Armaan]]'' and ''[[Josh: Independence Through Unity|Josh]]''\n*[[Faran Tahir]] \u2013 actor; born in the U.S. but was raised in Pakistan\n*[[Dilshad Vadsaria]] \u2013 of Portuguese and Pakistani descent; television actress, ''[[Greek (TV series)|Greek]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dilshadvadsaria.com/index.php/about |title=About |publisher=Dilshad Vadsaria |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcfamily.go.com/abcfamily/path/section_Shows+Greek/page_Detail |title=ABC Family \u2013 Greek \u2013 Official TV Show Site |publisher=Abcfamily.go.com |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>\n*[[GQ (actor)|Gregory J. Qaiyum]] \u2013 stage name GQ, American actor of German, English and Pakistani descent<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gqtheman.com/g_bio.php |title=Q Brothers Productions \u2013 GQ : bio |publisher=Gqtheman.com |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Iqbal Theba]] \u2013 starred in numerous American sitcoms but most famous for playing [[Principal Figgins]] on the show ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''\n*[[Krewella|Jahan Yousaf]] \u2013 part of EDM duo [[Krewella]]\n*[[JAQ (b-boy)|Jeffery A. Qaiyum]] \u2013 stage name JAQ; American professional b-boy of German, English and Pakistani descent\n*[[Lazarus (rapper)|Dr. Kamran Rashid Khan]] \u2013 stage name [[Lazarus (rapper)|Lazarus]], physician and rapper from [[Detroit]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pakhiphop.com/2009/06/mc-lazarus-rapper-and-docter.html |title=Welcome to Pakistans Hip Hop Music Scene: MC Lazarus, Rapper and Doctor |publisher=Pakhiphop.com |date=June 9, 2009 |accessdate=October 26, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110321090856/http://www.pakhiphop.com/2009/06/mc-lazarus-rapper-and-docter.html |archive-date=March 21, 2011 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n[[File:Lazarus (rapper).jpeg|thumb|Kamran Rashid Khan, also known as Lazarus, is a graduate of [[Wayne State University]].]]\n*[[Kamran Pasha]] \u2013 Hollywood screenwriter and director; wrote the Showtime hit series ''[[Sleeper Cell (TV miniseries)|Sleeper Cell]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kamranpasha.com/kamran_pasha.php |title=Kamran Pasha, Author of Mother of the Believers |publisher=Kamranpasha.com |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Kumail Nanjiani]] \u2013 actor and [[comedian]], ''[[Franklin & Bash]]''\n*[[Lubna Agha]] \u2013 artist\n*[[Mehr Hassan]] \u2013 Indian father, Pakistani mother; actress, model and classical dancer<ref>{{cite web|url=https: