April \u2013 ''[[On the Couch (2013 TV series)|On the Couch]]'' (2013)\n*May \u2013 ''[[Premier Soccer Saturday]]'' (1998\u20132013)\n*13 June \u2013 ''[[Come Dine With Me (Ireland)|Come Dine with Me]]'' (2011\u20132013) and ''[[Celebrity Come Dine with Me (Ireland)|Celebrity Come Dine with Me]]'' (2012\u20132013)\n*August \u2013 ''[[The Big Money Game]]'' (2008\u20132013)\n*30 August - ''The Hit'' (2013)\n*27 September - ''[[The Morning Show with Sybil & Martin]]'' (2009\u20132013)\n*October - ''[[Monday Night Soccer]]'' (2008-2013)\n\n==Deaths==\n\n*27 January \u2013 [[\u00c9amon de Buitl\u00e9ar]], 83, writer, and film and documentary maker<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-21228088 |work=BBC News |title=Irish wildlife filmmaker Eamon de Buitlear dies |publisher=BBC |date=28 January 2013 |accessdate=28 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2013 in Ireland]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{Years in TV by country|2013}}\n\n==2014==\n===January===\n*6 January \u2013 [[TV3 (Ireland)|TV3]] announces the shortlist of production companies contending to make the broadcaster's first soap opera or continuing drama.<ref>{{cite news|first=Joyce |last=Fegan |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/tv3-could-poach-some-fair-city-stars-for-their-new-home-grown-soap-29891669.html |title=TV3 could poach some Fair City stars for their new home grown soap |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=6 January 2014 |accessdate=10 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/featureinterviews/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4286728&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=TV3\u2019s Production Company Drama Shortlist |publisher=The Irish Film and Television Network |date=6 January 2014 |accessdate=10 January 2014}}</ref>\n*7 January \u2013 The [[Broadcasting Authority of Ireland]] (BAI) will not proceed with a licensing process for commercial digital terrestrial television, while a report commissioned by the regulator has suggested that without expansion, [[Saorview]] would become economically nonviable by the 2020s.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2014/0107/496388-bai-digital-tv/ |title=BAI will not launch commercial digital TV licence |work=RT\u00c9 News |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=7 January 2014 |accessdate=10 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Slattery |first=Laura |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/business/sectors/media-and-marketing/saorview-future-questioned-as-regulator-abandons-commercial-dtt-1.1647571 |title=Saorview future questioned as regulator abandons commercial DTT |newspaper=The Irish Times |publisher=The Irish Times Trust |date=8 January 2014 |accessdate=10 January 2014}}</ref>\n*12 January \u2013 The ''[[Irish Independent]]'' reports that TV3 has sold ''[[Tallafornia]]'' to the UK's [[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]] for broadcast in that country.<ref>{{cite news|first=Nick |last=Webb |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/irish/tv3-sells-hit-series-tallafornia-to-uks-channel-5-29907748.html |title=TV3 sells hit series 'Tallafornia' to UK's Channel 5 |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=12 January 2014 |accessdate=12 January 2014}}</ref>\n*12 January \u2013 ''[[The Sunday Times]]'' reports that TV3 have \"voiced grave concerns\" to the Broadcasting Authority of Ireland about UTV's plans to establish a TV channel in the Republic of Ireland, amid concerns it would not be subject to the same obligations as RT\u00c9 and TV3.<ref>{{cite news|first=Samantha |last=McCaughren |url=http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/news/ireland/article1361699.ece |title=TV3 will oppose UTV Irish licence |publisher=News International |newspaper=The Sunday Times |date=12 January 2014 |accessdate=2 February 2014 |url-access=subscription }}</ref>\n*15 January \u2013 [[Ryanair]] launch their \"thank you for flying\" ad campaign on TV3, with plans to treble their advertising budget in 2014.<ref>{{cite news|last=Slattery 