 Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=26 November 2014 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n*30 December \u2013 Desmond Fisher, 94, journalist, broadcaster and former head of [[RT\u00c9 News and Current Affairs|current affairs with RT\u00c9]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2015/01/05/former-catholic-herald-editor-desmond-fisher-dies/ |title=Former Catholic Herald editor Desmond Fisher dies |newspaper=The Catholic Herald |date=5 January 2015 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2014 in Ireland]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{Years in TV by country|2014}}\n\n==2015==\n===January===\n*1 January \u2013 [[UTV Ireland]], the country's first new commercial broadcaster since the launch of [[TV3 (Ireland)|TV3]] in 1998, goes on air at 7.25pm. The opening night includes an hour-long episode of ''[[Emmerdale]]'' and a New Year special presented by [[Pat Kenny]]. With the channel's launch, programmes such as ''Emmerdale'', ''[[Coronation Street]]'' and ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'' have moved from TV3 after UTV Ireland secured their broadcasting rights from its rival.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.irishmirror.ie/whats-on/arts-culture-news/utv-ireland-launch-happened-updates-4904572|title= UTV Ireland launch as it happened|date=1 January 2015 |work=Irish Mirror|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Stuart |last=Kemp |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jan/05/utv-ireland-becomes-republics-first-new-commercial-broadcaster-since-1998 |title=UTV Ireland becomes Republic's first new commercial broadcaster since 1998 |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=5 January 2015 |accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref>\n*4 January \u2013 ''[[Charlie (TV series)|Charlie]]'', a drama about the private life of former Taoiseach [[Charles Haughey]], debuts on [[RT\u00c9 One]]. The first episode is watched by an audience of 724,000.<ref>{{cite news|first=Mal |last=Rogers |url=http://www.irishpost.co.uk/entertainment/700000-tune-new-rte-drama-charles-haughey |title=Over 700,000 tune in to new RT\u00c9 drama on Charles Haughey |publisher= |work=The Irish Post |date=6 January 2015 |accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref>\n*5 January \u2013 RT\u00c9 One begins ''We Need to Talk About Porn'', a two-part documentary looking at the extent and impact of pornography consumption in Ireland.<ref name=\"RT\u00c9 Ten\"/>\n*5 January \u2013 [[UTV Ireland]]'s national news service, ''[[Ireland Live]]'', launches.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://utv.ie/Press/2015/01/04/Ireland-Live-News-launches-tomorrow-25837 |title=Ireland Live News launches tomorrow |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=4 January 2015 |accessdate=27 March 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316180047/http://utv.ie/Press/2015/01/04/Ireland-Live-News-launches-tomorrow-25837 |archivedate=16 March 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Kim |last=Bielenberg |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/review-utvs-new-ireland-live-is-slick-but-prepackaged-30884895.html |title=REVIEW: UTV's new 'Ireland Live' is slick but pre-packaged |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=6 January 2015 |accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>\n*7 January \u2013 New soap ''[[Red Rock (TV series)|Red Rock]]'' begins on TV3.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.irishmirror.ie/whats-on/arts-culture-news/red-rock-your-guide-tv3s-4921123|title= Red Rock: Your Guide |date=5 January 2015 |work=Irish Mirror|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref>\n*8 January \u2013 ''[[The Guarantee]]'', Colin Murphy's film about the [[Post-2008 Irish banking crisis|Irish banking crisis]], receives its world television premiere on TV3 at 9.00 p.m.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tv3.ie/entertainment_article.php?locID=1.803.813&article=155335 |title=\u2018The Guarantee\u2019 World Television Premiere on TV3 |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 Entertainment |publisher=TV3 |date=6 January 2015 |a