dy |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=28 January 2015 |accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref>\n*28 January \u2013 In [[Cork (city)|Cork]], an edition of Vincent Browne's Peoples Debate descends into uproar when a member of the audience miss-chooses his words while discussing the upcoming [[2015 Irish constitutional referendums|same-sex marriage referendum]], then goes into a rant about the morals of Ireland's political parties when his error is pointed out to him. Footage of the debate subsequently becomes popular on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Brian |last=O'Reilly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/mans-outburst-on-same-sex-marriage-leaves-vincent-browne-in-stitches-30947793.html |title=Man\u2019s outburst on same sex marriage leaves Vincent Browne in stitches |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=29 January 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref>\n*30 January \u2013 TV3 axes its afternoon show ''[[Late Lunch Live]]'' in favour of an evening chat show. ''The 7 O'Clock Show'' will air from 16 February, and will be presented by ''Late Lunch Live'' presenters [[Lucy Kennedy]] and [[Martin King (weather presenter)|Martin King]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.carlow-nationalist.ie/2015/01/30/tv3-says-goodbye-to-late-lunch-live/ |title=TV3 says goodbye to \u2018Late Lunch Live\u2019 |publisher= |newspaper=Carlow Nationalist |date=30 January 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205011234/http://www.carlow-nationalist.ie/2015/01/30/tv3-says-goodbye-to-late-lunch-live/ |archivedate=5 February 2015 }}</ref>\n*30 January \u2013 UTV Ireland secures a deal with [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] to show ''[[Good Morning Britain (2014)|Good Morning Britain]]'' after complaints from viewers who had watched the show on [[UTV (TV channel)|UTV]] via [[UPC Ireland|UPC]]. The programme had been absent from the platform since UTV I