ration with the Gaelic language television channel [[TG4]] that will see ''[[The SpongeBob Movie: Sponge Out of Water]]'' made available in the [[Irish language]] in cinemas, the first collaboration of its kind.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288052&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=New Spongebob film to be made available in Irish language in cinemas nationwide |publisher=Irish Film and Television Network |date=25 February 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref>\n*26 February \u2013 The TV3 Group confirms plans to launch TV3 HD on both [[UPC Ireland]] and [[Sky Ireland]] in August.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/sport/tv3-announce-strong-line-up-for-rugby-world-cup-coverage-663935.html |title=TV3 announce strong line-up for Rugby World Cup coverage |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=26 February 2015 |accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref>\n*26 February \u2013 TV3 confirms its intention to air all 48 matches from the [[2015 Rugby World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tv3.ie/entertainment_article.php?locID=1.803.813&article=160069 |title=TV3 confirms all 48 Rugby World Cup games |publisher=TV3 |work=TV3 News |date=26 February 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402120420/http://www.tv3.ie/entertainment_article.php?locID=1.803.813&article=160069 |archivedate=2 April 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n*27 February \u2013 Singer\u2013songwriter [[Molly Sterling]] is selected to [[Ireland in the Eurovision Song Contest 2015|represent Ireland]] in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2015]] with the song \"[[Playing with Numbers]]\".<ref name=\"Independent-2015-02-28\">{{cite news|first=Brian |last=Byrne |first2=Geraldine |last2=Gittens |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/teen-pianist-16-to-represent-ireland-at-60th-eurovision-song-contest-31029201.html |title=Teen pianist (16) to represent Ireland at 60th Eurovision Song Contest |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=28 February 2015 |accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> Sterling, who at 17 is Ireland's youngest Eurovision entry, is knocked out of the contest during the second semi-final on 21 May.<ref>{{cite news|last=Babbage |first=Rachel |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a648706/eurovision-song-contest-2015-ireland-malta-and-portugal-are-out-after-semi-final-2.html#~pdpQy35r6tHuNz |title=Eurovision Song Contest 2015: Ireland, Malta and Portugal are out after semi-final 2 |publisher= |work=Digital Spy |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-32842220 |title=Eurovision: Ireland and Portugal out |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=22 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n===March===\n*1 March \u2013 The ''Sunday Independent'' reports that RT\u00c9 and TV3 are allowing representatives of commercial brands to appear on daytime chat shows to sell their products as part of package deals ranging from \u20ac1,000 to \u20ac15,000 per appearance. The sale of \"editorial airtime\" is prohibited by the broadcasting regulations.<ref>{{cite news|first=Allison |last=Bray |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/rte-guests-charged-thousands-to-flog-brands-on-chat-show-31030846.html |title=RTE 'guests' charged thousands to flog brands on chat show |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Sunday Independent |date=1 March 2015 |accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref>\n*1 March \u2013 Writing in the ''Sunday Independent'', [[Gaelic Athletics Association|GAA]] analyst and former [[All-Ireland Senior Football Championship|All-Ireland]] winner [[Joe Brolly]] expresses his concern over the 2014 deal that allows [[Sky Sports]] to air some matches on a pay-per-view basis, saying that it \u201cexemplifies the disregard for the lifeblood\u201d of the GAA.<ref name=\"RT\u00c9-2015-03-02\"/> However, speaking to RT\u00c9 the following day, the new president of the Association, [[Aog\u00e1n \u00d3 Fearghail]] says that the deal has not hurt viewing figures and broadened the reach of [[Gaelic football]] by allowing it to be aired to a greater audience, but suggests that now there may be too many televised matches and the number may have to be reduced.<ref name=\"RT\u00c9-2015-03-02\">{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/2015/0302/683878-new-gaa-president-hints-at-reduced-tv-coverage/ |title=New GAA president hints at reduced TV coverage |work=RT\u00c9 Sport |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=2 March 2015 |accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref>\n*4 March \u2013 TV3's ''Red Rock'' tackles the issue of [[arranged marriage]] with the arrival of two Asian characters, a father and daughter in conflict over the topic.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tv3-soap-red-rock-tackles-issue-of-arranged-marriage-in-controversial-storyline-31033237.html |title=TV3 soap Red Rock tackles issue of arranged marriage in controversial storyline |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=2 March 2015 |accessdate=2 March 2015}}</ref>\n*4 March \u2013 RT\u00c9 launches RT\u00c9 Player International, an online service making the broadcaster's content available to international viewers.<ref>{{cite news|first=Caroline |last=Stephens |url=http://www.rte.ie/blogs/digital/2015/03/04/rte-launches-new-global-online-irish-television-service-for-international-audiences/ |title=RT\u00c9 Launches New Global Online Irish Television Service for International Audiences |work=RT\u00c9 Digital |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=4 March 2015 |accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>\n*5 March \u2013 As figures reveal that audience figures for UTV's ''Ireland Live'' dropped from 1.5 million in January to 1.3 million in February, [[Kevin Bakhurst]], the managing director of news and current affairs at RT\u00c9, tells the ''[[The Herald (Ireland)|Evening Herald]]'' UTV face a \"hard slog\" to improve their audience numbers.<ref>{{cite news|first=Elaine |last=McCahill |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/utv-in-for-long-hard-slog-warns-rte-chief-kevin-bakhurst-31042300.html |title=UTV in for long, hard slog, warns RT\u00c9 chief Kevin Bakhurst |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Evening Herald |date=5 March 2015 |accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref>\n*5 March \u2013 John Martin, a member of the New Land League, says he will make an official complaint to Garda\u00ed following a confrontation with broadcaster Vincent Browne outside a repossessed property in [[Killiney]] the previous day. Gorse Hill Manor has been occupied by the group since it was seized by the High Court. Brown was accompanied by a camera crew and journalists, and used footage of his visit on that evening's edition of his show, ''[[Tonight with Vincent Browne]]''.<ref>{{cite news|first=Paul |last=Healy |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/news/new-land-league-member-to-make-official-complaint-to-gardai-about-tv3-broadcaster-vincent-browne-31043331.html |title='New Land League' member to make official complaint to gardai about TV3 broadcaster Vincent Browne |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=5 March 2015 |accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref>\n*5 March \u2013 TV3 announces it is axing the live element of its entertainment series, ''[[Xpos\u00e9]]'', which will return to being pre-recorded. The decision will allow the broadcaster to develop ''The 7 O'Clock Show'' as a live show with a similar format to [[BBC One]]'s ''[[The One Show]]''.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tv3s-xpos-live-axed-after-just-six-months-to-accommodate-live-seven-oclock-show-31043228.html |title=TV3's Xpos\u00e9 Live axed after just six months to accommodate live Seven O'Clock show |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=5 March 2015 |accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref>\n*7 March \u2013 The ''Irish Independent'' reports that the Commercial Court is to hear a case brought against TV3 by RT\u00c9 for non-payment of transmission tariffs through 2013 and 2014. The tariffs relate to unpaid fees to 2RN, a subsidiary company of RT\u00c9 that manages the transmission system. The case is scheduled for Monday 9 March.<ref>{{cite news|first=Colm |last=Kelpie |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/irish/rte-and-tv3-in-legal-dispute-31047565.html |title=RTE and TV3 in legal dispute |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=7 March 2015 |accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref>\n*7 March \u2013 A group of 150 protesters gather outside RT\u00c9's Donnybrook headquarters to demonstrate against their coverage of [[Anti-austerity protests in Ireland|water protests]] and austerity measures.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2015/0307/685326-protesters/ |title=Up to 150 protesters gather outside RT\u00c9 |work=RT\u00c9 News |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=7 March 2015 |accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref>\n*8 March \u2013 The US drama ''[[American Crime (TV series)|American Crime]]'' debuts on RT\u00c92, just three days after making its US television debut on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Pat |last=Stacey |url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/it-would-be-a-crime-to-miss-out-on-this-compelling-drama-31055346.html |title=It would be a crime to miss out on this compelling drama |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Evening Herald |date=10 March 2015 |accessdate=8 April 2015}}</ref>\n*8 March \u2013 [[Mary McAleese]] narrates a documentary about the women's organisation [[Cumann na mBan]] on TG4.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0226/683098-tg4-screens-new-cumann-na-mban-documentary/ |title=TG4 to screen new Cumann na mBan documentary |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=26 February 2015 |accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref>\n*9 March \u2013 At the Commercial Court, RT\u00c9 is seeking \u20ac1m from TV3 for the non payment of digital transmission tariffs through 2013 and 2014.<ref>{{cite news|first=Tim |last=Healy |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/courts/rte-suing-tv3-for-around-1m-in-dispute-over-alleged-failure-to-pay-for-digital-transmission-services-31052754.html |title=RTE suing TV3 for around \u20ac1m in dispute over alleged failure to pay for digital transmission services |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=9 March 2015 |accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>\n*10 March \u2013 In celebration of [[St Patrick's Day]], UTV Ireland launches its \"Bringing U Home\" campaign, which encourages Irish people living overseas to submit greetings videos to friends and relatives, with entries having a chance to win return air tickets to Ireland from wherever they are currently living.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.westmeathindependent.ie/news/roundup/articles/2015/03/10/4036256--utv-ireland-wants-to-bring-you-home-for-st-patricks-day/ |newspaper=Westmeath Independent |title=UTV Ireland wants to bring you home for St Patrick's Day |publisher= |date=10 March 2015 |accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>\n*11 March \u2013 Analysis of All-Ireland matches from the past five seasons has indicated that Sky Sports succession as second provider of GAA games has had little impact on the majority of supporters as many county matches are not shown live.<ref>{{cite news|first=Martin |last=Breheny |url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/skys-arrival-has-altered-very-little-for-majority-of-gaa-fans-31060274.html |title=Sky's arrival has altered very little for majority of GAA fans |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=11 March 2015 |accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>\n*14 March \u2013 [[Brendan O'Connor (media personality)|Brendan O'Connor]] confirms that the current series of ''[[The Saturday Night Show]]'' will be the last. O'Connor will return with a new show in 2016, while [[Ray D'Arcy]] will present a replacement show for ''The Saturday Night Show'' from the autumn.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0314/687145-oconnor-announces-end-of-saturday-night-show/ |title=O'Connor announces end of Saturday Night Show |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=14 March 2015 |accessdate=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n*18 March \u2013 UTV Media confirms it expects UTV Ireland to report \u00a36m in losses over 2015, double its original forecast. The company cites the length of time the channel took to receive its public service status as a major contributing factor, since it could not fully engage with advertisers and viewers until it was established.<ref>{{cite news|first=Mark |last=Sweney |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/mar/18/utv-media-doubles-forecast-for-losses-to-6m |title=UTV Ireland\u2019s forecast losses double to \u00a36m |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=18 March 2015 |accessdate=18 March 2015}}</ref>\n*18 March \u2013 TV3 will host two [[Irish Film and Television Awards]] ceremonies this year. The first in May will focus on film and television, while the second in October will award achievements in the television industry.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0318/688011-tv3-to-host-2015-iftas/ |title=TV3 to host two IFTA Awards this year |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=18 March 2015 |accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref>\n*18 March \u2013 ''GAA USA'', a four-part series presented by [[Dara \u00d3 Cinn\u00e9ide]] that tells the story of [[Gaelic games in North America|Gaelic football in the United States]], debuts on TG4.<ref>{{cite news|first=Steve |last=Neville |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/examviral/fun-times/video-new-documentary-explores-the-gaas-history-in-the-us-317794.html |title=New docum