ondon}}</ref>\n*22 March \u2013 RT\u00c9 screens Ireland's [[2015 Women's Six Nations Championship]] match against Scotland live from Cumbernauld.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/rugby/six-nations/rte-to-show-ireland-women-against-scotland-as-they-chase-six-nations-and-triple-crown-glory-31077502.html |title=RTE to show Ireland women against Scotland as they chase Six Nations and Triple Crown glory |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=18 March 2015 |accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref> The game sees Ireland beat Scotland 37-3, meaning Ireland have secured both the 2015 Men's and Women's Six Nations titles.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/rugby/six-nations/2015/0322/688907-ireland-women-six-nations/ |title=Ireland obliterate Scotland to win Six Nations |work=RT\u00c9 Sport |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=22 March 2015 |accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref>\n*24 March \u2013 TV3 announces the launch of its new nightly news programme, ''[[TV3 News at 8]]'', a 30-minute bulletin showing at 8.00pm, following a similar format to nightly newscasts across Europe. The programme goes on air from Monday 30 March, and will be presented by [[Colette Fitzpatrick]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tv3-launches-new-main-evening-news-at-8pm-31091956.html |title=TV3 launches new main evening news at 8pm |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=24 March 2015 |accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n*25 March \u2013 Speaking at a sitting of the [[D\u00e1il \u00c9ireann|D\u00e1il]], former Communications Minister [[Pat Rabbitte]] accuses RT\u00c9 of being a \"recruiting sergeant\" for [[Sinn F\u00e9in]] and the far left because of its coverage of the Irish Water controversy. The comments are rejected by the broadcaster and Sinn F\u00e9in.<ref>{{cite news|first=Niall |last=O'Connor |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/rt-is-recruiting-sergeant-for-sinn-fin-says-rabbitte-31095639.html |title=RT\u00c9 is 'recruiting sergeant' for Sinn F\u00e9in, says Rabbitte |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=26 March 2015 |accessdate=24 May 2015}}</ref>\n*26 March \u2013 [[Director-General of the BBC|BBC Director-General]] [[Tony Hall, Baron Hall of Birkenhead|Tony Hall]] signs a deal with [[Northern Ireland Screen]] which will see an increase in network spending in Northern Ireland. The agreement will also enable an extra \u00a3200,000 a year to be invested in drama development, and a \u00a32m annual investment in children\u2019s content.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kanter |first=Jake |url=http://www.broadcastnow.co.uk/news/bbc-unveils-boost-for-ni-television-sector/5085804.article |title=BBC unveils boost for NI television sector &#124; News &#124; Broadcast |publisher= |work=Broadcast |date=27 March 2015 |accessdate=11 April 2015}}</ref>\n*27 March \u2013 TV3 has announced the establishment of a strategic distribution partnership with [[Sky Vision]], which will see its content distributed on the international market.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288155&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=TV3 partners with Sky Vision in major international distribution deal |publisher=The Irish Film and Television Network |date=27 March 2015 |accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n*29 March \u2013 [[Minister for Communications (Ireland)|Minister for Communications]]  [[Alex White (Irish politician)|Alex White]] will include the [[Six Nations Championship]] on a list of sporting events that must be made [[free-to-air]] on live terrestrial television, it is reported.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cuddihy |first=Tony |url=http://www.joe.ie/sport/the-six-nations-to-be-made-free-to-air-on-irish-television/490104 |title=The Six Nations to be made 'free-to-air' on Irish television |publisher=JOE.ie |date=29 March 2015 |accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref> White confirms to Cabinet his intention to add the coverage of the tournament to the free-to-air list two days later.<ref>{{cite news|first=Raf |last=Diallo |url=http://www.newstalk.com/Six-Nations-moves-closer-to-freetoair-future |title=Six Nations moves closer to free-to-air future |publisher=Communicorp |work=Newstalk |date=31 March 2015 |accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref>\n*30 March \u2013 [[Sky Sports]] have secured the rights to Ireland's [[2015 Rugby World Cup]] warm-up games against Scotland on 15 August, and Wales on 29 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/soccer/world-cup/at-least-three-of-irelands-four-rugby-world-cup-warmup-games-to-be-shown-on-sky-sports-31105119.html |title=At least three of Ireland's four Rugby World Cup warm-up games to be shown on Sky Sports |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=30 March 2015 |accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref>\n*30 March \u2013 Former RT\u00c9 presenter [[Sheena Keane]] makes her return to television five years after leaving ''[[The Afternoon Show]]'' with a series on TV3 titled ''Get the Numbers, Write''.<ref>{{cite news|last=McCahill |first=Elaine |url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/sheana-returns-to-tv-five-years-after-quitting-rte-31103697.html |title=Sheana returns to TV five years after quitting RT\u00c9 |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Evening Herald |date=30 March 2015 |accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref>\n*30 March \u2013 Following a case brought by three music companies, the High Court orders UPC Ireland, the country\u2019s second largest internet service provider, to take measures to stop the illegal downloading of content.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://advanced-television.com/2015/03/30/judge-upc-ireland-must-enforce-3-strikes-policy/ |title=Judge: UPC Ireland \u2018must enforce 3 strikes policy\u2019 |publisher=Advanced Television |date=30 March 2015 |accessdate=11 April 2015}}</ref>\n*31 March \u2013 David McGovern, a fireman based in West Florida, is announced as the winner of UTV Ireland's \"Bringing U Home\" competition, and wins return tickets to visit his friends and relatives in Ireland.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://utv.ie/News/2015/03/31/UTV-Ireland-is-bringing-David-McGovern-home-34620 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402114836/http://utv.ie/News/2015/03/31/UTV-Ireland-is-bringing-David-McGovern-home-34620 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2 April 2015 |title=UTV Ireland is bringing David McGovern home |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=31 March 2015 |accessdate=31 March 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===April===\n*1 April \u2013 In an [[April Fools' Day]] hoax RT\u00c9 News reports the launch of Fur TV, a channel aimed specifically at pets.<ref>{{cite news|first=Laura |last=Delaney |url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0401/691320-watch-new-tv-channel-for-pets-is-launched-today/ |title=New TV channel for pets is launched |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=1 April 2015 |accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref> On TV3, [[Vincent Browne]] joins [[Glenda Gilson]] to present the channel's entertainment series Xpos\u00e9.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/examviral/real-life/video-the-incredibly-uncomfortable-moment-vincent-browne-hosts-xposeacute-322597.html |title=The incredibly uncomfortable moment Vincent Browne hosts Xpose |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=7 April 2015 |accessdate=2 May 2015}}</ref>\n*2 April \u2013 RT\u00c9 have issued a memorandum to their staff reminding them not to publicly express any opinions about the forthcoming [[2015 Irish constitutional referendums|22 May referendum]] during the campaign period, including via posts on social media, it is reported.<ref>{{cite news|first=Louise |last=Hogan |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/media/rte-staff-warned-not-to-post-views-on-samesex-marriage-referendum-on-social-media-31114268.html |title=RTE staff warned not to post views on same-sex marriage referendum on social media |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=2 April 2015 |accessdate=6 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Elaine |last=McCahill |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/rtes-gagging-order-broadcaster-warns-staff-not-to-make-comment-on-marriage-referendum-31115766.html |title=RTE's gagging order: Broadcaster warns staff not to make comment on marriage referendum |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=3 April 2015 |accessdate=6 April 2015}}</ref>\n*2 April \u2013 [[SIPTU]] general secretary [[Jack O'Connor (trade unionist)|Jack O'Connor]] walks off the set of TV3's ''[[Tonight with Vincent Browne]]'' following a heated argument with Brown. O'Connor exited the studio because he believed his presence legitimised TV3's policy of not respecting the rights of its staff in [[collective bargaining]], but Browne described the union leader's actions as a \"stroke\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/watch-tv3s-vincent-browne-accuses-siptu-boss-of-stunt-after-he-walks-off-show-live-on-air-31115723.html |title=Watch: TV3's Vincent Browne accuses SIPTU boss of 'stunt' after he walks off show live on air |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=3 April 2015 |accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref>\n*3 April \u2013 Pat Cowap, the director of RT\u00c9's soon to end ''The Saturday Night Show'', is recruited by UTV Ireland to work on Pat Kenny's new show ''In The Round'', which begins filming shortly.<ref>{{cite news|first=Kirsty |last=Blake Knox |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/pat-kenny-woos-director-of-axed-saturday-night-show-for-new-slot-on-utv-31117505.html |title=Pat Kenny woos director of axed 'Saturday Night Show' for new slot on UTV |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=4 April 2015 |ac