ay \u2013 Figures released by UPC Ireland indicate the number of subscribers to the service has fallen from 422,700 to 386,500 over the past twelve months. The operator blames an increase in competition for the fall. However, its broadband business is faring better, with an increase from 348,300 to 365,800 subscribers over the same period.<ref>{{cite news|first=Adrian |last=Weckler |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/technology/news/upc-sees-big-switchoff-in-its-irish-tv-business-31207478.html |title=UPC sees big switch-off in its Irish TV business |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=9 May 2015 |accessdate=9 May 2015}}</ref>\n*10 May \u2013 RT\u00c9 One airs a service of remembrance for the 40 children killed during the Easter Rising, which took place on 7 May at St Patrick's Parish Church, [[Ringsend]], Dublin.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0507/699462-rte-to-air-service-to-remember-children-of-1916/ |title=RT\u00c9 to air service to remember children of 1916 |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=7 May 2015 |accessdate=9 May 2015}}</ref>\n*11 May \u2013 ''[[Pat Kenny in the Round]]'' debuts on UTV Ireland.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288256&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=Pat Kenny returns to TV on May 11 with UTV Ireland entertainment series |work=The Irish Film and Television Network |publisher= |date=30 April 2015 |accessdate=30 April 2015}}</ref> The first show to be aired features an interview with  [[Tyrone GAA]] manager [[Mickey Harte]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://utv.ie/Entertainment/2015/05/08/Mickey-Harte-first-guest-on-Pat-Kenny-in-the-Round-36891 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518093146/http://utv.ie/Entertainment/2015/05/08/Mickey-Harte-first-guest-on-Pat-Kenny-in-the-Round-36891 |url-status=dead |archive-date=18 May 2015 |title=Mickey Harte first guest on Pat Kenny in the Round |publisher=U