out the \"potential conflict of interest\" such a move would create.<ref>{{cite news|first=John |last=Downing |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/rt-in-firing-line-over-miriam-ocallaghans-ambitions-for-presidency-31351224.html |title=RT\u00c9 in firing line over Miriam O'Callaghan's 'ambitions for Presidency' |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=4 July 2015 |accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref> RT\u00c9 subsequently says that it has procedures in place to avoid a conflict of interest if such an instance were to arise.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/rte-to-ensure-no-conflict-of-interest-if-miriam-ocallaghan-runs-for-aras-31363592.html |title=RTE to ensure \u2018no conflict of interest\u2019 if Miriam O'Callaghan runs for Aras |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Evening Herald |date=9 July 2015 |accessdate=9 July 2015 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*9 July \u2013 Emma Murphy, a 26-year-old mother from Dublin whose online video in which she spoke about suffering domestic abuse at the hands of her partner went viral within hours of being posted, gives her first television interview to [[Elaine Crowley (presenter)|Elaine Crowley]] on TV3's ''[[Midday (Irish TV series)|Midday]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/entertainment-news/172012/Emma-Murphy-opens-up-to-TV3s-Elaine-Crowley-on-Midday |title=Emma Murphy opens up to TV3\u2019s Elaine Crowley on Midday |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 |publisher=TV3 |date=9 July 2015 |accessdate=9 July 2015}}</ref>\n*12 July \u2013 The ''Sunday Independent'' reports a forecast from UK investment firm Peel Hunt that UTV Ireland's continuing losses could force it into a merger with TV3 within a year.<ref>{{cite news|first=Harry |last=Leech |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/irish/utv-ireland-may-merge-with-tv3-after-mounting-losses-31369068.html |title=UTV Ireland may merge wi