/30/Frampton-title-defence-fight-to-air-live-on-UTV-Ireland-40084 |title=Frampton title defence fight to air live on UTV Ireland |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=30 June 2015 |accessdate=30 June 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703000211/http://utv.ie/Sport/2015/06/30/Frampton-title-defence-fight-to-air-live-on-UTV-Ireland-40084 |archivedate=3 July 2015 }}</ref>\n*18 July \u2013 The ''Irish Independent'' reports that former model and ''Total Xposure'' contestant [[Ruth O'Neill]], who left Ireland in 2010 to pursue a television presenting career in the United States, will return to present RT\u00c9's new entertainment series, ''Bounce''.<ref>{{cite news|first=Freya |last=Drohan |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/ruth-oneill-returns-to-ireland-for-new-presenting-role-on-rte-31386276.html |title=Ruth O'Neill returns to Ireland for new presenting role on RTE |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=18 July 2015 |accessdate=19 July 2015}}</ref>\n*19 July \u2013 [[Land Rover]] Ireland have paid TV3  \u20ac450,000 to be the channel's official sponsorship partner of the [[2015 Rugby World Cup]], the ''Sunday Independent'' reports.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sarah |last=McCabe |url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/rugby/world-cup/land-rover-pays-450000-to-sponsor-tv3s-coverage-of-rugby-world-cup-31386861.html |title=Land Rover pays \u20ac450,000 to sponsor TV3's coverage of Rugby World Cup |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Sunday Independent |date=19 July 2015 |accessdate=19 July 2015}}</ref>\n*21 July \u2013 UTV Ireland announces it will broadcast the [[Ernst & Young Entrepreneur of the Year Award]], beginning in September.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/utv-ireland-to-broadcast-entrepreneur-of-the-year-tv-series-31392262.html |title=UTV Ireland to broadcast Entrepreneur of the Year TV series |