's Den]]'' has appeared on television for twenty years.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/ian-dempsey-returning-to-tv-after-20-years-with-stint-on-tv3-31471410.html |title=Ian Dempsey returning to TV after 20 years with stint on TV3 |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Sunday Independent |date=23 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*25 August \u2013 Figures obtained under Freedom of Information rules reveal that RT\u00c9 spent \u20ac2 million on travel expenses for its staff in 2014, as well as \u20ac425,000 on wardrobe expenses over the same period.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sharon |last=McGowan |first2=Emma Jane |last2=Hade |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/media/behind-the-news-rte-spends-425k-on-wardrobe-for-stars-31475529.html |title=Behind the news: RTE spends \u20ac425k on wardrobe for stars |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=25 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*28 August \u2013 UTV Media, the parent company of UTV Ireland, reports a 90% fall in pre-tax profits as costs at the new channel reach \u00a312m.<ref>{{cite news|first=Mark |last=Sweney |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/aug/28/utvs-profits-fall-90-as-new-tv-channel-costs-mount |title=UTV's profits fall 90% as new TV channel costs mount |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=28 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*28 August \u2013 Launch of the weekend version of TV3's ''[[Ireland AM]]''. ''Saturday AM'' is presented by [[Anna Daly]] and [[Simon Delaney]], while ''Sunday AM'' sees Daly co-presenting alongside [[Ivan Yates]].<ref>{{cite news|first=John |last=Meagher |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/lifestyle/artsfilmtv/filmandtv/anna-daly-fronts-tv3s-new-weekend-morning-showsaturday-am-and-sunday-am-350839.html |title=Anna Daly fronts TV3's new weekend morning show Saturday AM and Sunday AM |publis