 Independent |date=3 September 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*2 September \u2013 Unveiling their autumn schedule, TV3 announce that it has signed Brian and Pippa Ormond as presenters. The announcement comes a day after Ormonde inadvertently revealed to RT\u00c9 that he will present a new game show for TV3.<ref>{{cite news|last=De Burca |first=Demelza |url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/showbiz/irish-showbiz/tv3-sign-brian-ormond-wife-6371646 |title=TV3 sign Brian Ormond and wife Pippa in surprise double deal in move that will shock RTE |newspaper=Irish Mirror |publisher=Trinity Mirror |date=3 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref> Among the programming in the broadcaster's forthcoming schedule are two documentary series about the murders of [[Sophie Toscan du Plantier]] and Karen Buckley.<ref>{{cite news|first=Evelyn |last=Ring |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/ireland/tv3-to-air-documentaries-on-du-plantier-and-karen-buckley-murders-351671.html |title=TV3 to air documentaries on du Plantier and Karen Buckley murders |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=3 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*2 September \u2013 TV3 airs ''Marilyn Monroe: The Missing Evidence'', a one-off documentary looking at some of the conspiracy theories surrounding the [[death of Marilyn Monroe]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/entertainment-news/176978/TV3-airs-special-uncovering-new-information--about-Marilyn-Monroes-death |title=TV3 airs special uncovering new information about Marilyn Monroe\u2019s death |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 |publisher=TV3 |date=31 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*2 September \u2013 TV3 reveals that it has signed former [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] footballer [[Graeme Souness]] to join their Champions League analysis team.<ref>{{cite news|first=Larry |last=Ryan |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/soccer/tv3-snap-