d out of the debate, which is broadcast two days later.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/vincent-browne-peoples-debate-clontarf-castle-2317802-Sep2015/ |title=Garda\u00ed called after Vincent Browne debate descends into mayhem |publisher=Thejournal.ie |date=8 December 2015 |accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=David |last=Kearns |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/tv3-to-edit-out-chaotic-scenes-after-vincent-browne-debate-ends-in-threats-31514827.html |title=TV3 to edit out 'chaotic scenes' after Vincent Browne debate ends in threats |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=9 September 2015 |accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref>\n*10 September \u2013 [[Irish Film and Television Awards|IFTA]] confirms a three-year deal with Irish retailer [[Gala (supermarket)|Gala]] to sponsor the [[Irish Film and Television Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288599&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=IFTA announce Gala as the Headline Sponsor for the annual Television Awards |publisher=The Irish Film & Television Network |date=10 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*11 September \u2013 Official launch of the IFTA Gala Television Awards, which will take place on 22 October at Dublin's Double Tree Hotel.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/rep_bodies/repbodiesnews/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288606&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=IFTA Gala Television Awards is launched |publisher=The Irish Film & Television Network |date=11 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*14 September \u2013 UTV Ireland launches a new on-screen branding featuring people such as farmers, tattoo artists and designers with the strapline \u201cYOU TV\u201d. UTV hopes the new look will \"reinvigorate\" the brand.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/utv-new-look-rebrand-2328469-Sep2015/ |title=