2/0516/1224316195063.html |title=Taoiseach rules out TV3 treaty debate with Adams |newspaper=The Irish Times |publisher=The Irish Times Trust |date=16 May 2012 |accessdate=24 May 2012}}</ref>\n* 15 May \u2013 TV3 cancels ''[[The Apprentice (Irish TV series)|The Apprentice]]'', meaning it will not return for a fifth series.<ref>{{cite news|first=Ken |last=Sweeney |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/bill-cullen-told-youre-fired-by-tv3-as-station-pulls-the-plug-on-irish-the-apprentice-3109990.html |title=Bill Cullen told 'You're Fired' by TV3 as station pulls the plug on Irish 'The Apprentice' |newspaper=Irish Independent |publisher=Independent News and Media |date=16 May 2012 |accessdate=24 May 2012}}</ref>\n* 29 May \u2013 The [[Government of the United Kingdom|UK Government]] confirms that television viewers in [[Northern Ireland]] will be able to watch [[RT\u00c9 One]], [[RT\u00c9 Two]] and [[TG4]] on [[Freeview (UK)|Freeview]] following the [[UK digital transition|digital switchover]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-northern-ireland-18246907 |work=BBC News |title=RT\u00c9 channels will go on Freeview in Northern Ireland |publisher=BBC |date=29 May 2012 |accessdate=4 June 2012}}</ref>\n* 29 May \u2013 RT\u00c9 apologises after it emerged a member of staff airbrushed the logo of a TV3 microphone during a news report on the 27 May edition of the ''[[RT\u00c9 News: Nine O'Clock|Nine O'Clock News]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.herald.ie/news/redfaced-rte-sorry-for-airbrushing-out-tv3-logo-3123124.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120904182613/http://www.herald.ie/news/redfaced-rte-sorry-for-airbrushing-out-tv3-logo-3123124.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=4 September 2012 |title=Red-faced RT\u00c9 sorry for airbrushing out TV3 logo |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=Evening Herald |date=29 May 2012 |accessdate=31 May 2012 }}</ref>\n* 31 May \u2013 [[Director-General of RT\u00c9|RT\u00c9 Director-General]] [[Noel Curran]] warns that the broadcaster is considering pay cuts and the cessation of certain services if it does not secure \u20ac25 million of cost reduction measures.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2012/0531/director-general-warns-rte-staff-of-pay-cuts.html|title=Director General Noel Curran warns RT\u00c9 staff of pay cuts and compulsory redeployment|date=31 May 2012|work=RT\u00c9 News|publisher=RT\u00c9|accessdate=31 May 2012}}</ref>\n* 31 May \u2013 ''[[The Irish Times]]'' reports that TV3 has invested in \u201c[[Metrocam]]\u201d technology that enables its journalists to broadcast live images without access to a [[satellite van]]. Instead the camera has a radio frequency transmitter which allows video and audio to be relayed wirelessly to its studios via a transmission station.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/finance/2012/0531/1224316983327.html |title=TV3 cameras let out of shackles |newspaper=The Irish Times |publisher=The Irish Times Trust |date=31 May 2012 |accessdate=4 June 2012}}</ref>\n\n===June===\n* 7 June \u2013 ''The Irish Times'' reports that upgrades are planned for [[RT\u00c9 Player]] and [[3Player]] to make viewing from mobile devices and slower broadband connections much easier.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/finance/2012/0607/1224317439066.html |title=RT\u00c9 and TV3 to enhance catch-ups |newspaper=The Irish Times |publisher=The Irish Times Trust |date=7 June 2012 |accessdate=15 June 2012}}</ref>\n* 10 June \u2013 The [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]]'s opening match against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] at [[UEFA Euro 2012]] attracted the biggest television audience for a sports event in Ireland since 1994.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/2012/0611/repofireland.html|title=2.3 million watch Ireland's Euro 2012 opener|date=11 June 2012|work=RT\u00c9 Ten|publisher=RT\u00c9|accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref>\n* 23 June \u2013 The Clare County Board is to write to Croke Park, expressing concern over the manner in which Clare [[hurling]] manager [[Davy Fitzgerald]] was treated on the 17 June edition of RT\u00c9's ''[[The Sunday Game]]'', which discussed remarks he made to a Waterford player during that day's [[Munster Senior Club Hurling Championship|Munster]] semi-final in [[Thurles]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Martin |last=Breheny |url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/hurling/clare-backing-fitz-in-rte-row-3147074.html |title=Clare backing Fitz in RT\u00c9 row |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=Irish Independent |date=23 June 2012 |accessdate=23 June 2012}}</ref>\n\n===July===\n* 6 July \u2013 50th anniversary of the first edition of ''[[The Late Late Show (Ireland)|The Late Late Show]]''.\n* 7 July \u2013 It is reported that TV3 will write directly to Taoiseach Enda Kenny to reject a suggestion that he was assaulted by reporter [[Ursula Halligan]] following an incident at the [[National Library of Ireland|National Library]] on 4 July in which Kenny tripped over a flower pot as he attempted to evade Halligan's questions. The incident prompted a complaint from Kenny's staff.<ref>{{cite news|first=Kevin |last=Doyle |url=http://www.herald.ie/news/tv3-fights-back-at-claim-reporter-assaulted-kenny-3161353.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130217192403/http://www.herald.ie/news/tv3-fights-back-at-claim-reporter-assaulted-kenny-3161353.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=17 February 2013 |title=TV3 fights back at claim reporter 'assaulted' Kenny |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=Evening Herald |date=7 July 2012 |accessdate=9 July 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=John |last=Drennan |first2=Maeve |last2=Sheehan |url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/martin-to-challenge-kenny-over-spin-doctor-ursula-assault-claim-3161605.html |title=Martin to challenge Kenny over spin doctor 'Ursula assault' claim |newspaper=Sunday Independent |publisher=Independent News and media 