=RT\u00c9 News |date=23 July 2014 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n*10 August \u2013 [[Ann Rowan]], 85, actress (''[[The Riordans]]'', ''[[Father Ted]]'').<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2014/0811/636368-the-riordans-actress-ann-rowan-has-died/ |title=The Riordans actress Ann Rowan has died |publisher=RT\u00c9 |work=RT\u00c9 News |date=11 August 2014 |accessdate=11 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150211142256/http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2014/0811/636368-the-riordans-actress-ann-rowan-has-died/ |archivedate=11 February 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n*13 October \u2013 Gabrielle Reidy, 54, actress<ref>{{cite news|first=Michael |last=Coveney |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2014/oct/15/gabrielle-reidy |title=Gabrielle Reidy obituary |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=15 October 2014 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n*19 October \u2013 [[Gerard Parkes]], 90, actor.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/arts/gerard-parkes-fraggle-rock-actor-dead-at-90-1.2805925 |title=Gerard Parkes, Fraggle Rock actor, dead at 90 |publisher=CBC |work=CBC News |date=20 October 2014 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n*10 November \u2013 [[Brian Farrell (broadcaster)|Brian Farrell]], 85, political broadcaster and academic<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/former-rte-broadcaster-brian-farrell-has-died-at-85-30732057.html |title=Former RT\u00c9 broadcaster Brian Farrell has died at 85 |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=10 November 2014 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n*13 November \u2013 Paddy MacHugh, first [[RT\u00c9|Telef\u00eds \u00c9ireann]] weather forecaster<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.superannrte.ie/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4434:death-of-paddy-machugh-former-rte-weather-forecaster&catid=18:bereavements-1400&Itemid=103 |title=Death of Paddy MacHugh (Former RT\u00c9 Weather Forecaster) |publisher=Superannrte |date=13 November 2014 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n*26 November \u2013 Anita Notaro, author and former television director<ref>{{cite news|first=Geraldine |last=Gittens |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/news/irish-author-anita-notaro-dies-after-long-illness-30777399.html |title=Irish author Anita Notaro dies after long illness |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=26 November 2014 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n*30 December \u2013 Desmond Fisher, 94, journalist, broadcaster and former head of [[RT\u00c9 News and Current Affairs|current affairs with RT\u00c9]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2015/01/05/former-catholic-herald-editor-desmond-fisher-dies/ |title=Former Catholic Herald editor Desmond Fisher dies |newspaper=The Catholic Herald |date=5 January 2015 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2014 in Ireland]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{Years in TV by country|2014}}\n\n[[Category:2014 in Irish television|2014 in Irish television]]\n\n==2015==\n===January===\n*1 January \u2013 [[UTV Ireland]], the country's first new commercial broadcaster since the launch of [[TV3 (Ireland)|TV3]] in 1998, goes on air at 7.25pm. The opening night includes an hour-long episode of ''[[Emmerdale]]'' and a New Year special presented by [[Pat Kenny]]. With the channel's launch, programmes such as ''Emmerdale'', ''[[Coronation Street]]'' and ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'' have moved from TV3 after UTV Ireland secured their broadcasting rights from its rival.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.irishmirror.ie/whats-on/arts-culture-news/utv-ireland-launch-happened-updates-4904572|title= UTV Ireland launch as it happened|date=1 January 2015 |work=Irish Mirror|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Stuart |last=Kemp |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jan/05/utv-ireland-becomes-republics-first-new-commercial-broadcaster-since-1998 |title=UTV Ireland becomes Republic's first new commercial broadcaster since 1998 |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=5 January 2015 |accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref>\n*4 January \u2013 ''[[Charlie (TV series)|Charlie]]'', a drama about the private life of former Taoiseach [[Charles Haughey]], debuts on [[RT\u00c9 One]]. The first episode is watched by an audience of 724,000.<ref>{{cite news|first=Mal |last=Rogers |url=http://www.irishpost.co.uk/entertainment/700000-tune-new-rte-drama-charles-haughey |title=Over 700,000 tune in to new RT\u00c9 drama on Charles Haughey |publisher= |work=The Irish Post |date=6 January 2015 |accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref>\n*5 January \u2013 RT\u00c9 One begins ''We Need to Talk About Porn'', a two-part documentary looking at the extent and impact of pornography consumption in Ireland.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0105/669341-rte-tens-tv-picks-for-today-monday-january-5/ |title=RT\u00c9 TEN'S TV picks for today Monday January 5 |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=5 January 2015 |accessdate=27 June 2015}}</ref>\n*5 January \u2013 [[UTV Ireland]]'s national news service, ''[[Ireland Live]]'', launches.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://utv.ie/Press/2015/01/04/Ireland-Live-News-launches-tomorrow-25837 |title=Ireland Live News launches tomorrow |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=4 January 2015 |accessdate=27 March 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316180047/http://utv.ie/Press/2015/01/04/Ireland-Live-News-launches-tomorrow-25837 |archivedate=16 March 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Kim |last=Bielenberg |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/review-utvs-new-ireland-live-is-slick-but-prepackaged-30884895.html |title=REVIEW: UTV's new 'Ireland Live' is slick but pre-packaged |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=6 January 2015 |accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>\n*7 January \u2013 New soap ''[[Red Rock (TV series)|Red Rock]]'' begins on TV3.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.irishmirror.ie/whats-on/arts-culture-news/red-rock-your-guide-tv3s-4921123|title= Red Rock: Your Guide |date=5 January 2015 |work=Irish Mirror|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref>\n*8 January \u2013 ''[[The Guarantee]]'', Colin Murphy's film about the [[Post-2008 Irish banking crisis|Irish banking crisis]], receives its world television premiere on TV3 at 9.00 p.m.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tv3.ie/entertainment_article.php?locID=1.803.813&article=155335 |title=\u2018The Guarantee\u2019 World Television Premiere on TV3 |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 Entertainment |publisher=TV3 |date=6 January 2015 |accessdate=16 March 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150319140446/http://www.tv3.ie/entertainment_article.php?locID=1.803.813&article=155335 |archivedate=19 March 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n*10 January \u2013 New [[The National Lottery|National Lottery]] game show hosted by [[Nicky Byrne]], ''The Million Euro Challenge'', starts on [[RT\u00c9 One]]. The show is later cancelled after just one series.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.rte.ie/tv/programmes/themillioneurochallenge.html|title= A new tv gameshow presented by nicky byrne|date=5 January 2015 |work=RT\u00c9|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref>\n*12 January \u2013 Figures indicate that RT\u00c9 broadcast the 20 most watched television programmes of 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0112/671979-rte-broadcasts-all-top-20-shows-of-2014/ |title=RT\u00c9 broadcasts the top 20 shows in 2014 |publisher=RT\u00c9 |work=RT\u00c9 News |date=12 January 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n*15 January \u2013 Figures indicate RT\u00c9 broadcast the 20 most watched sports programmes of 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/sport/other-sport/2015/0115/672800-rte-tops-the-tables-for-sport-on-tv-in-2014/ |title=RT\u00c9 tops the tables for sport on TV in 2014 |publisher=RT\u00c9 |work=RT\u00c9 Sport |date=15 January 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n*18 January \u2013 ''[[Sunday Independent (Ireland)|The Sunday Independent]]'' reports that the decision by [[Sky (UK & Ireland)|Sky]] and [[UPC Ireland]] to increase their prices may have had a negative impact on UTV Ireland's launch because price rises coincided with the launch. UPC's decision to allocate UTV Ireland the same channel formerly occupied by Northern Ireland's [[UTV (TV channel)|UTV]] may also be affecting the channel because some of the content available through UTV is not shown by its counterpart.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sarah |last=McCabe |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/media/utv-blames-weak-ratings-on-sky-and-upc-s-price-hikes-30915637.html |title=UTV blames weak ratings on Sky and UPC's price hikes |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Sunday Independent |date=18 January 2015 |accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>\n*21 January \u2013 [[Sean Haughey]], the son of the late Taoiseach Charles Haughey, criticises the portrayal of his father in RT\u00c9's drama ''Charlie''.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sarah |last=Stack |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/family-of-charles-haughey-slam-tv-bosses-over-portrayal-in-charlie-30926019.html |title=Family of Charles Haughey slam TV bosses over portrayal in Charlie |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=21 January 2015 |accessdate=10 April 2015}}</ref>\n*27 January \u2013 The [[Broadcasting Authority of Ireland]] publishes a new code of programme standards designed to promote responsible broadcasting.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2015/0127/675913-bai/ |title=BAI aims to promote 'responsible broadcasting' with new code of standards |publisher=RT\u00c9 |work=RT\u00c9 News |date=27 January 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref>\n*28 January \u2013 John Whelan, chair of the support group Advic, criticises TV3 for what he feels to be a juvenile press release about [[State Pathologist's Office|State Pathologist]] [[Marie Cassidy]]'s appearance in an edition of the channel's ''[[The Restaurant (Irish TV series)|The Restaurant]]''. The press release begins by suggesting that Cassidy \"hopes to knock 'em dead on TV3's 'The Restaurant'\", which Whelan feels is inappropriate when her office deals with cases of murder and manslaughter.<ref>{{cite news|first=Mark |last=O'Regan |first2=Kirsty |last2=Blake Knox |first3=Adam |last3=Cullen |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tv3-in-hot-water-over-reality-show-with-pathologist-marie-cassidy-30943896.html |title=TV3 in hot water over reality show with pathologist Marie Cassidy |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=28 January 2015 |accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref>\n*28 January \u2013 In [[Cork (city)|Cork]], an edition of Vincent Browne's Peoples Debate descends into uproar when a member of the audience miss-chooses his words while discussing the upcoming [[2015 Irish constitutional referendums|same-sex marriage referendum]], then goes into a rant about the morals of Ireland's political parties when his error is pointed out to him. Footage of the debate subsequently becomes popular on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Brian |last=O'Reilly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/mans-outburst-on-same-sex-marriage-leaves-vincent-browne-in-stitches-30947793.html |title=Man\u2019s outburst on same sex marriage leaves Vincent Browne in stitches |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=29 January 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref>\n*30 January \u2013 TV3 axes its afternoon show ''[[Late Lunch Live]]'' in favour of an evening chat show. ''The 7 O'Clock Show'' will air from 16 February, and will be presented by ''Late Lunch Live'' presenters [[Lucy Kennedy]] and [[Martin King (weather presenter)|Martin King]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.carlow-nationalist.ie/2015/01/30/tv3-says-goodbye-to-late-lunch-live/ |title=TV3 says goodbye to \u2018Late Lunch Live\u2019 |publisher= |newspaper=Carlow Nationalist |date=30 January 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205011234/http://www.carlow-nationalist.ie/2015/01/30/tv3-says-goodbye-to-late-lunch-live/ |archivedate=5 February 2015 }}</ref>\n*30 January \u2013 UTV Ireland secures a deal with [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] to show ''[[Good Morning Britain (2014)|Good Morning Britain]]'' after complaints from viewers who had watched the show on [[UTV (TV channel)|UTV]] via [[UPC Ireland|UPC]]. The programme had been absent from the platform since UTV Ireland's launch.<ref>{{cite news|first=James |last=Mulhall |url=http://www.irishpost.co.uk/news/utv-ireland-to-show-good-morning-britain-after-viewers-dissatisfaction |title=UTV Ireland to show Good Morning Britain after viewers\u2019 dissatisfaction |publisher= |newspaper=The Irish Post |date=30 January 2015 |accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n===February===\n*1 February \u2013 [[Stephen Fry]] appears as a guest on RT\u00c9 One's religious affairs programme ''[[The Meaning of Life (TV series)|The Meaning of Life]]'' during which he makes controversial comments about [[God]], of whom he says is \"utterly evil, capricious and monstrous\".<ref>{{cite news|first=Henry |last=McDonald |url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2015/feb/01/stephen-fry-god-evil-maniac-irish-tv |title=Stephen Fry calls God an \u2018evil, capricious, monstrous maniac\u2019 |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=1 February 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n*2 February \u2013 ''Good Morning Britain'' debuts on UTV Ireland, but viewing figures give it an average audience of 2,700, compared to 61,000 for TV3's ''[[Ireland AM]]''.<ref>{{cite news|first=Gavin |last=McLoughlin |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/not-such-a-good-morning-as-british-breakfast-show-attracts-just-2700-viewers-to-utv-ireland-30964880.html |title=Not such a good morning as British breakfast show attracts just 2,700 viewers to UTV Ireland |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=5 February 2015 |accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 [[Sky (UK & Ireland)|Sky]] reports an increase of more than 200,000 customers in the UK and Ireland in the second half of 2014, its highest growth for nine years.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-31125858 |title=Sky sees strong customer growth |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=4 February 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 The [[National Lottery (Ireland)|National Lottery]] midweek draw is postponed until the following day because of a computer glitch that stopped the ticket machines working.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2015/0204/677849-lottery/ |title=\u20ac10m jackpot delay as Lotto postponed for first time |publisher=RT\u00c9 |work=RT\u00c9 News |date=4 February 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 It is announced that Jeff Ford will leave his role as [[TV3 (Ireland)|TV3]]'s Director of Content in April to take up the position of General Manager at [[Fox International Channels UK]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tv3-director-of-content-jeff-ford-leaving-group-for-fox-international-channels-uk-30964393.html |title=TV3 director of content Jeff Ford leaving group for Fox International Channels UK |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=4 February 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 Viewing figures for TV3's new soap ''[[Red Rock (TV series)|Red Rock]]'' have halved from 323,000 to 165,000 during its first three weeks of broadcasting. However, TV3 remains pleased with the soap's performance, saying that its viewership has surpassed expectations.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/viewing-figures-for-new-tv3-soap-red-rock-halve-in-three-weeks-30964439.html |title=Viewing figures for new TV3 soap 'Red Rock' halve in three weeks |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=4 February 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 TV3 presenter [[Sybil Mulcahy]] announces she is leaving the channel after 16 years.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/i-need-a-new-challenge-says-sybil-mulcahy-as-she-takes-tv3-redundancy-after-16-years-30963058.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150204221324/http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/i-need-a-new-challenge-says-sybil-mulcahy-as-she-takes-tv3-redundancy-after-16-years-30963058.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=4 February 2015 |title=\u2018I need a new challenge,\u2019 says Sybil Mulcahy as she takes TV3 redundancy after 16 years |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Evening Herald |date=4 February 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015 }}</ref>\n*5 February \u2013 RT\u00c92 confirms it will air ''[[Eurovision Song Contest's Greatest Hits|Eurovision's Greatest Hits]]'', a concert celebrating 60 years of the [[Eurovision Song Contest]], which will be shown throughout Europe over the Easter weekend.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0205/677984-rte2-to-air-eurovisions-greatest-hits/ |title=RT\u00c92 to air Eurovision's Greatest Hits |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=5 February 2015 |accessdate=8 April 2015}}</ref>\n*9 February \u2013 [[Setanta Sports]] announces that it has gained exclusive live broadcasting rights to [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] and [[Europa League]] football for three years from 2015\u201316. However, RT\u00c9 has retained the television and online rights to show Wednesday Champions League matches, while TV3 will show Tuesday Champions League matches.<ref>{{cite news|first=Brynmor |last=Pattison |url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/sport/soccer/soccer-news/setanta-sports-gains-television-rights-5133120 |title=Setanta Sports gains television rights for Champions League and exclusive rights for Europa League |publisher=Trinity Mirror |newspaper=The Irish Mirror |date=9 February 2015 |accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n*9 February \u2013 A man who appears in the TV3 documentary series ''Prison Families'' is given a suspended sentence at Dublin's Circuit Criminal Court after his trial was told that a robbery and an attempted robbery he committed took place at the time of other offences, and should have been considered at a previous trial.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sonya |last=McLean |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/courts/star-of-tv3-show-avoids-jail-over-raid-on-hair-salon-30977087.html |title=Star of TV3 show avoids jail over raid on hair salon |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=9 February 2015 |accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref>\n*12 February \u2013 Viewing figures released by Tam Ireland and Nielsen indicate UTV Ireland had an average audience of 5.5% through January, with an episode of ''Coronation Street'' featuring a storyline involving a bus crash having the most number of viewers, with 597,000.<ref>{{cite news|first=Laura |last=Slattery |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/business/media-and-marketing/utv-ireland-takes-5-5-share-of-tv-viewing-in-january-1.2101418 |title=UTV Ireland takes 5.5% share of TV viewing in January |publisher=The Irish Times Trust |newspaper=The Irish Times |date=12 February 2015 |accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n*13 February \u2013 UTV Ireland announces its intention to air highlights of the [[Ireland cricket team]]'s [[2015 Cricket World Cup|2015 World Cup]] campaign, beginning with their opening match against the [[West Indies cricket team|West Indies]] on 16 February.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/other-sports/utv-ireland-to-televise-highlights-of-irelands-cricket-world-cup-campaign-30990412.html |title=UTV Ireland to televise highlights of Ireland's Cricket World Cup campaign |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=13 February 2015 |accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n*14 February \u2013 [[Vodafone]] unveil plans to launch a TV service to compete with UPC, Sky and [[Eircom]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Adrian |last=Weckler |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/irish/vodafone-plans-tv-service-in-ireland-as-quad-play-beckons-30992612.html |title=Vodafone plans TV service in Ireland as 'quad play' beckons |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=15 February 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref>\n*15 February \u2013 UTV Ireland considers a move for its 6.30pm bulletin of ''Ireland Live'' to take on TV3's ''[[TV3 News]]'' at 5.30pm because of poor viewing figures, which were as low as 2% for the first two weeks of January.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sarah |last=McCabe |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/utv-ireland-may-switch-flagship-news-show-to-take-on-tv3-30992620.html |title=UTV Ireland may switch flagship news show to take on TV3 |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Sunday Independent |date=15 February 2015 |accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>\n*16 February \u2013 [[Laura Whitmore]] announces that she is leaving MTV News after seven years.<ref>{{cite news|first=Freya |last=Drohan |url=http://independent.ie/entertainment/television/its-been-a-blast-laura-whitmore-leaving-mtv-after-seven-years-30995718.html |title='It's been a blast': Laura Whitmore leaving MTV after seven years |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=16 February 2015 |accessdate=6 October 2015}}</ref>\n*18 February \u2013 The [[BBC Northern Ireland]] current affairs series ''[[Spotlight (NI)|Spotlight]]'' wins \"Scoop of the Year\" at the [[Royal Television Society Awards]] for its programme ''A Woman Alone With The IRA'', an investigation into how the IRA handled sexual abuse allegations against a suspected member.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-northern-ireland-31529097 |title=BBC NI Spotlight wins RTS award for Mairia Cahill scoop |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=18 February 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref>\n*18 February \u2013 UTV Ireland confirms it will be showing [[Carl Frampton]]'s prize fight against [[Chris Avalos]] on 28 February after UPC viewers, whose access to UTV ended with the launch of its all-Ireland counterpart, expressed concerns it would not be available.<ref>{{cite news|last=Nolan |first=Sean |url=http://www.sportsjoe.ie/boxing/great-news-as-utv-ireland-confirm-they-will-broadcast-carl-framptons-title-fight/14043 |title=Great news as UTV Ireland confirm they will broadcast Carl Frampton's title fight |publisher=SportsJOE.ie |date=18 February 2015 |accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>\n*19 February \u2013 [[Taoiseach]] [[Enda Kenny]] uses ''[[Prime Time (Irish TV programme)|Prime Time]]'' to submit to a rare live television interview but must wait as an episode of British soap opera ''[[EastEnders]]'' concludes.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/enda-kenny-prime-time-2-1949421-Feb2015/|title=Taoiseach on a rare one-on-one interview live on TV|work=TheJournal.ie|date=19 February 2015|accessdate=19 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150304230552/http://www.thejournal.ie/enda-kenny-prime-time-2-1949421-Feb2015/|archivedate=4 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://businessetc.thejournal.ie/enda-kenny-interview-rescheduled-eastenders-1949132-Feb2015/|title=RT\u00c9 has delayed the Taoiseach\u2019s interview\u2026 because of EastEnders|work=Business, etc.|date=19 February 2015|accessdate=19 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150304230831/http://businessetc.thejournal.ie/enda-kenny-interview-rescheduled-eastenders-1949132-Feb2015/|archivedate=4 March 2015}}</ref>\n*20 February \u2013 [[Ryan Tubridy]]'s tone and choice of questions when interviewing [[Anti-Austerity Alliance]] TD [[Paul Murphy (Irish politician)|Paul Murphy]] in relation to the campaign against the implementation of a water tax on ''[[The Late Late Show (Ireland)|The Late Late Show]]'' is much criticised.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.broadsheet.ie/2015/02/22/the-paul-murphy-takedown/|title=The Paul Murphy Takedown (contains transcript of interview)|date=22 February 2015|accessdate=22 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225143855/http://www.broadsheet.ie/2015/02/22/the-paul-murphy-takedown/|archivedate=25 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Robert|last=Hynes|url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/news/irish-news/twitter-users-angered-ryan-tubridys-5203545|title=Twitter users angered by Ryan Tubridy's interview with Anti Austerity Alliance TD Paul Murphy|date=21 February 2015|accessdate=21 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225143953/http://www.irishmirror.ie/news/irish-news/twitter-users-angered-ryan-tubridys-5203545|archivedate=25 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Julien|last=Mercille|authorlink=Julien Mercille|url=http://www.broadsheet.ie/2015/02/23/just-doing-his-job/|title=Just Doing His Job|date=23 February 2015|accessdate=23 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225143717/http://www.broadsheet.ie/2015/02/23/just-doing-his-job/|archivedate=25 February 2015}}</ref>\n*23 February \u2013 Undecided on whether to renew ''[[The Voice of Ireland]]'' for a fifth series, RT\u00c9 are looking for an alternative to replace the programme for its Winter 2016 schedule.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/rte-seeking-alternatives-to-the-voice-of-ireland-for-2016-sunday-tv-slot-31014850.html |title=RTE seeking alternatives to The Voice of Ireland for 2016 Sunday TV slot |publisher=Independent News and Media |n