evision, while the second in October will award achievements in the television industry.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0318/688011-tv3-to-host-2015-iftas/ |title=TV3 to host two IFTA Awards this year |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=18 March 2015 |accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref>\n*18 March \u2013 ''GAA USA'', a four-part series presented by [[Dara \u00d3 Cinn\u00e9ide]] that tells the story of [[Gaelic games in North America|Gaelic football in the United States]], debuts on TG4.<ref>{{cite news|first=Steve |last=Neville |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/examviral/fun-times/video-new-documentary-explores-the-gaas-history-in-the-us-317794.html |title=New documentary explores the GAA's history in the US |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=11 March 2015 |accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Stephen |last=Glennon |url=http://connachttribune.ie/tg4-documentary-charts-history-of-gaa-in-the-usa-777/ |title=TG4 documentary charts history of GAA in the USA |publisher= |newspaper=Connacht Tribune |date=20 March 2015 |accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref>\n*19 March \u2013 Lynda McQuaid is appointed Director of Content at TV3, replacing Jeff Ford.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/new-head-of-content-tv3-2001830-Mar2015/ |title=The woman behind You\u2019re A Star gets top job at TV3 |publisher=Distilled Media |work=Thejournal.ie |date=19 March 2015 |accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref>\n*20 March \u2013 Broadcaster [[Joe Duffy]] is making a television version of his popular radio programme, ''Liveline'', a pilot of which will be aired by RT\u00c9 over the summer.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/rtes-joe-duffy-set-to-make-tv-version-of-his-hit-radio-show-liveline-31081812.html |title=RTE's Joe Duffy set to make TV version of his hit radio show 'Liveline' |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=20 March 2015