Rising]], is held in Dublin's [[O'Connell Street]]. The occasion includes a screening of ''Insurrection'', the broadcaster's eight-part drama that was commissioned for the Easter Rising's 50th anniversary in 1966.<ref>{{cite news|first=David |last=Kearns |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/festivals/oconnell-street-transformed-for-road-to-the-rising-showcase-31120672.html |title=O'Connell Street transformed for \u2018Road to the Rising\u2019 showcase |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=6 April 2015 |accessdate=6 April 2015}}</ref>\n*7 April \u2013 The [[Irish Language Broadcast Fund]] announces its latest round of funding for television and film projects, which includes finance for ''Piobair\u00ed Ard Mhacha'', a series for [[BBC Northern Ireland]] about the [[Armagh Pipers]], and ''Lomax in \u00c9irinn: The Album That Saved Irish Music'', a series about the field collectors of folk music [[Alan Lomax]] for TG4.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/finance/finance_news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288179&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=Irish Language Broadcast Fund announce latest funding decisions |publisher=The Irish Film and Television Network |date=7 April 2015 |accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref>\n*8 April \u2013 Viewers are invited to apply for tickets for ''Pat Kenny In The Round'', which goes on air in May.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/audience-tickets-for-pat-kennys-new-utv-ireland-show-now-available-31127352.html |title=Audience tickets for Pat Kenny's new UTV Ireland show now available |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=8 April 2015 |accessdate=8 April 2015}}</ref>\n*8 April \u2013 TV3 Group announce that the timeshift channel [[TV3 +1]] is launching on [[Sky (UK & Ireland)|Sky]] Channel 117 after they agreed a deal with Sky to carry the channel.<ref>{{cite news|first=Karina |last=Corbett |url=http://www.businessandleadership.com/marketing/item/50174-tv3-1-launches-at-channel/ |title=TV3+1 launches at channel 117 on Sky \u2013 Marketing \u2013 Marketing &#124; Ireland's online business and management news service |publisher=Distilled Media |work=Business and Leadership |date=9 April 2015 |accessdate=9 April 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150415140450/http://www.businessandleadership.com/marketing/item/50174-tv3-1-launches-at-channel/ |archivedate=15 April 2015 }}</ref>\n*9 April \u2013 ''[[The Unemployables]]'', which aired as a pilot in 2014, returns to [[RT\u00c92]] for a full series. The programme sees [[Darren Kennedy]] and [[Jennifer Maguire]] helping young unemployed people to find work.<ref>{{cite news|first=Anna |last=Nolan |url=http://www.herald.ie/opinion/anna-nolan-trying-to-convince-the-unemployed-that-they-deserve-a-chance-is-hard-work-31122355.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150407151534/http://www.herald.ie/opinion/anna-nolan-trying-to-convince-the-unemployed-that-they-deserve-a-chance-is-hard-work-31122355.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=7 April 2015 |title=Trying to convince the unemployed that they deserve a chance is hard work |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Evening Herald |date=7 April 2015 |accessdate=7 April 2015 }}</ref>\n*9 April \u2013 French international distributor, Lagard\u00e8re Entertainment has secured a deal to distribute TG4's Gaelic language thriller, ''[[The Gift (2014 film)|An Bronntanas]]'' on the international market.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288187&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=French Distributor to take \u2018An Bronntanas\u2019 worldwide |publisher=The Irish Film and Television Network |date=9 April 2015 |accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref>\n*9 April \u2013 The first edition of ''Pat Kenny in the Round'' is filmed at Dublin's [[Mansion House, Dublin|Mansion House]]. The programme takes the form of a one-hour interview with a notable figure, with the first guest being Canadian astronaut [[Chris Hadfield]]. It is the first in a series of thirteen interviews, though an airdate for the series is yet to be confirmed.<ref>{{cite news|first=John |last=Meagher |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/screen-test-can-pat-kenny-save-utv-ireland-31130327.html |title=Screen test... can Pat Kenny save UTV Ireland? |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Sunday Independent |date=12 April 2015 |accessdate=12 April 2015}}</ref> \n*12 April \u2013 An article in the ''Sunday Independent'' highlights some of the shows that ceased being available to many Irish television viewers following the launch of UTV Ireland. They include ITV's ''[[ITV News at Ten|News at Ten]]'' and Championship League football coverage, both of which have been replaced with homegrown programmes, as well as dramas such as ''[[Foyle's War]]'' and ''[[Arthur & George (TV series)|Arthur & George]]''.<ref>{{cite news|first=John |last=Meagher |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/reschedule-the-favourites-utv-ireland-has-turned-off-31130335.html |title=Reschedule: the favourites UTV Ireland has turned off |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Sunday Independent |date=12 April 2015 |accessdate=26 April 2015}}</ref>\n*15 April \u2013 Debut of ''[[Wild Ireland]]'', a six-part series presented by [[Christine Bleakley]] in which she travels the [[Wild Atlantic Way]], the longest continuous coastal route.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/broadcast/BroadcastNews/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288180&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=Big Mountain\u2019s \u2018Wild Ireland\u2019 to air on ITV and UTV Ireland |publisher=The Irish Film and Television Network |date=7 April 2015 |accessdate=7 April 2015}}</ref>\n*15 April \u2013 ''Islanders'', a four-part series looking at life in the island communities on the Irish coast, debuts on TV3.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/new-tv3-series-to-shed-light-on-island-life-31142394.html |title=New TV3 series to shed light on island life |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=14 April 2015 |accessdate=14 April 2015}}</ref>\n*16 April \u2013 It is reported that a number of private equity groups, including [[The Carlyle Group]], have held preliminary discussions with TV3's owners, [[Doughty Hanson]] about a possible takeover.<ref>{{cite news|first=Mark |last=Kleinman |url=http://news.sky.com/story/1466127/buyout-firms-broadcast-bids-for-irelands-tv3 |title=Buyout Firms Broadcast Bids For Ireland's TV3 |publisher=British Sky Broadcasting |work=Sky News |date=16 April 2015 |accessdate=16 April 2015}}</ref>\n*16 April \u2013 TV3 begins airing ''Paramedics'', a six-part documentary looking at the work of Ireland's emergency medical service.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288197&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=Tile Films \u2018Paramedics\u2019 to air on TV3 on Thursday, 16 April |publisher=The Irish Film and Television Network |date=14 April 2015 |accessdate=14 April 2015}}</ref>\n*20 April \u2013 Premiere of ''D\u00e1il on the Dole'', a four-part TV3 series that sees [[Teachta D\u00e1la|TDs]] spending time with constituents on social welfare in order to gain insight into the issues affecting them.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tv3.ie/entertainment_article.php?locID=1.803.813&article=164760 |title=Dail on the Dole |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 Entertainment |publisher=TV3 |date=20 April 2015 |accessdate=20 April 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150427143116/http://www.tv3.ie/entertainment_article.php?locID=1.803.813&article=164760 |archivedate=27 April 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Ed |last=Power |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/t