3&rid=4288256&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=Pat Kenny returns to TV on May 11 with UTV Ireland entertainment series |work=The Irish Film and Television Network |publisher= |date=30 April 2015 |accessdate=30 April 2015}}</ref> The first show to be aired features an interview with  [[Tyrone GAA]] manager [[Mickey Harte]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://utv.ie/Entertainment/2015/05/08/Mickey-Harte-first-guest-on-Pat-Kenny-in-the-Round-36891 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518093146/http://utv.ie/Entertainment/2015/05/08/Mickey-Harte-first-guest-on-Pat-Kenny-in-the-Round-36891 |url-status=dead |archive-date=18 May 2015 |title=Mickey Harte first guest on Pat Kenny in the Round |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=8 May 2015 |accessdate=9 May 2015 }}</ref> The programme is well received by viewers, but is beaten in the ratings by RT\u00c9 One's ''[[Claire Byrne Live]]'', which features a debate on the upcoming marriage referendum between [[Simon Coveney]] TD for the Yes campaign and Senator [[R\u00f3n\u00e1n Mullen]] for the No campaign. An average 150,000 tune in for Pat Kenny's show at 9.00pm, UTV Ireland's best figures to date for the 9.00pm timeslot and a 33% increase in viewership, while Claire Byrne's programme at 9.35 receives an average audience of 368,000.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/rtes-claire-byrne-live-hits-ratings-high-as-pat-kenny-in-the-round-launches-on-utv-ireland-31215974.html |title=RTE's Claire Byrne Live hits ratings high as Pat Kenny in the Round launches on UTV Ireland |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=12 May 2015 |accessdate=12 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Independent-2015-05-19\">{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tonight-with-vincent-browne-to-broadcast-second-marriage-referendum-debate-31235772.html |title=Tonight with Vincent Browne to broadcast second marriage referendum debate |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=19 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref>\n*11 May \u2013 ''Ireland Live''{{'}}s [[Alison Comyn]] chairs a marriage referendum debate from UTV Ireland's Cork studios, featuring representatives from Mothers and Fathers Matter, Yes Equality, Stand Up for Marriage and Labour LGBT.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://utv.ie/News/2015/05/11/Marriage-referendum-debated-live-on-UTV-Ireland-37039 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150515000048/http://utv.ie/News/2015/05/11/Marriage-referendum-debated-live-on-UTV-Ireland-37039 |url-status=dead |archive-date=15 May 2015 |title=Marriage referendum debated live on UTV Ireland |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=11 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015 }}</ref>\n*11 May \u2013 TV3's ''Tonight with Vincent Browne'' features a live debate from the Headfort Arms Hotel in [[Kells, County Meath|Kells]]. A man is seen falling over as Browne introduces the programme, prompting him to comment on the fact to much raucous laughter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/watch-somebody-faceplants-behind-vincent-browne-live-on-air-31214892.html |title=Somebody faceplants behind Vincent Browne live on air |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=12 May 2015 |accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Flaherty |first=Ciara |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/examviral/fun-times/a-man-fell-over-on-vincent-browne-last-night-and-a-nation-cheered-330116.html |title=A man fell over on Vincent Browne last night and a nation cheered |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=12 May 2015 |accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref>\n*12 May \u2013 TV3 announces it will air the [[2015 FA Cup Final]] on 30 May, bringing the [[FA Cup]] back to Irish terrestrial television after a 20-year absence.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/tv-new