earing-on-darcy-show-rt-31224300.html |title=We didn't block Kenny from appearing on D'Arcy show \u2013 RT\u00c9 |publisher=Independent News and Media |date=15 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref>\n*16 May \u2013 ''The Irish Independent'' reports that Communications Minister Alex White is to replace Health Minister [[Leo Varadkar]] as the government representative in the final RT\u00c9 marriage referendum debate after a row broke out between Fine Gael and the [[Labour Party (Ireland)|Labour Party]] about which of the coalition parties should be represented in the final debate, the government's place in the two previous debates having been taken by Fine Gael TDs.<ref>{{cite news|first=Niall |last=O'Connor and Lise Hand |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/referendum/varadkar-is-frozen-out-of-referendum-debate-despite-protests-from-rt-chiefs-31227217.html |title=Varadkar is frozen out of referendum debate, despite protests from RT\u00c9 chiefs |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=16 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref>\n*18 May \u2013 ''[[Thejournal.ie]]'' reports that [[Fianna F\u00e1il]]\u2014currently the main [[Opposition Front Bench (Ireland)|opposition party]]\u2014has written to RT\u00c9 to complain about its exclusion from the majority of the broadcaster's marriage referendum debates. [[Sinn F\u00e9in]] have said they will also complain about their exclusion from the debates.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/fianna-fail-sinn-fein-rte-2109135-May2015/ |title=Fianna F\u00e1il and Sinn F\u00e9in are really unhappy with RT\u00c9 |publisher=Distilled Media |work=Thejournal.ie |date=18 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref>\n*18 May \u2013 Communications Minister Alex White, who is to represent the government in the last of three marriage referendum debates, to be aired by RT\u00c9 the following day, dismisses claims of government tension after RT\u00c9 said that Health Minister [[Leo Varadkar]], who is openly gay, had originally been lined up to appear.<ref>{{cite news|first=John |last=Downing |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/referendum/alex-white-says-leo-varadkar-has-no-issue-about-television-debate-lineup-31231389.html |title=Alex White says Leo Varadkar 'has no issue' about television debate line-up |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=19 May 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2015}}</ref> White goes head-to-head with R\u00f3n\u00e1n Mullen on a ''[[Prime Time (Irish TV programme)|Prime Time]]'' special presented by [[Miriam O'Callaghan (media personality)|Miriam O'Callaghan]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/late-slot-costs-claire-in-tv-wars-31240540.html |title=Late slot costs Claire in TV wars |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref> while Varadkar speaks for the Yes campaign opposite [[Patrick Treacy]] SC on the 18 May edition of ''Claire Byrne Live'', the second edition of that programme to feature a marriage referendum debate.<ref name=\"Independent-2015-05-19\"/> \n*18 May \u2013 UTV's ''Ireland Live at 10'' hosts a debate on the Age of Presidential Candidates referendum from its [[Galway]] studios.<ref name=\"UTV-2015-05-08\"/>\n*18 May \u2013 The second guest on ''Pat Kenny In the Round'' is Canadian astronaut Chris Hadfield. Figures later indicate the programme to have had an audience of 66,000, fewer than half the viewers who tuned into the previous week's opening edition. The show is beaten in the ratings for the 9.00pm timeslot by documentaries on both RT\u00c9 One and TV3\u2014''Ireland and the Eurovision'' attracting a viewership of 351,800 for RT\u00c9 One, and ''The Battle of Gorse Hill'', a documentary about businessman Brian O'Donnell, securing an audience of 74,700 for TV3. An edition of ''Coronation Street'' preceding ''In the Round'' pulls in an audience of 416,000.<ref>{{cite news|first=Kirsty |last=Blake Knox |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tv3-and-rt-trump-kennys-in-the-round-as-viewers-fall-by-over-50pc-31237497.html |title=TV3 and RT\u00c9 trump Kenny's 'In the Round' as viewers fall by over 50pc |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=20 May 2015 |accessdate=20 May 2015}}</ref>\n*19 May \u2013 A second marriage referendum debate on ''[[Tonight with Vincent Browne]]'' features Fianna F\u00e1il leader [[Miche\u00e1l Martin]] and journalist [[John Waters (journalist)|John Waters]].<ref name=\"Independent-2015-05-19\"/> Waters also debates with Sinn F\u00e9in deputy leader [[Mary Lou McDonald]] on UTV's ''[[Ireland Live]]''.<ref>{{cite news|first=Anita |last=McSorley |url=http://utv.ie/News/2015/05/19/McDonald-and-Waters-debate-marriage-referendum-37552 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522141733/http://utv.ie/News/2015/05/19/McDonald-and-Waters-debate-marriage-referendum-37552 |url-status=dead |archive-date=22 May 2015 |title=McDonald and Waters debate marriage referendum |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=19 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015 }}</ref>\n*21 May \u2013 As part of the [[Broadcasting Authority of Ireland]]'s code of practice relating to election coverage, a moratorium on the broadcast of news items that it is deemed could influence the decision of voters in the 22 May marriage referendum comes into effect at 2.00pm.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/broadcast-moratorium-in-effect-678152.html |title=Broadcast moratorium in effect |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2015}}</ref>\n*21 May \u2013 The High Court grants businessman Denis O'Brien an injunction against RT\u00c9 preventing them from broadcasting a news story about his banking affairs with [[Irish Bank Resolution Corporation]] (IBRC).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/obrien-wins-high-court-case-against-rte-678177.html |title=O'Brien wins High Court case against RTE |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2015}}</ref> The report must now be redacted before the High Court rules on whether a revised version can be aired.<ref>{{cite news|first=Tim |last=Healy |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/courts/denis-obrien-granted-high-court-injunction-preventing-rte-broadcast-31241859.html |title=Denis O'Brien granted High Court injunction preventing RTE broadcast |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2015}}</ref>\n*21 May \u2013 [[Charlie Murphy]], [[Brian Gleeson (actor)|Brian Gleeson]] and [[Sarah Greene (actress)|Sarah Greene]] will appear in a new RT\u00c9 drama about the [[Easter Rising]]. ''Rebellion'', a five-part television series produced by [[Zodiak Media|Zodiak Media Ireland]], will air in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/charlie-murphy-brian-gleeson-and-sarah-greene-to-star-in-new-rte-drama-series-rebellion-31241686.html |title=Charlie Murphy, Brian Gleeson and Sarah Greene to star in new RTE drama series 'Rebellion' |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288322&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=RT\u00c9 announces new Irish drama series \u2018Rebellion\u2019 |work=The Irish Film and Television Network |publisher= |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2015}}</ref>\n*21 May \u2013 TV3 announce their coverage of the [[12th Irish Film and Television Awards|2015 IFTA Film and Drama Awards]], which will be held on 24 May. Caroline Morahan will present the Awards coverage itself, while [[Louise Duffy]] and [[Eoghan Doherty]] will present a special TV3 IFTA Film and Drama Awards programme on Monday 1 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/tv-news/167571/Louise--Eoghan-to-present-special--TV3-IFTA-Film-and-Drama-Awards-programme |title=Louise & Eoghan to present special TV3 IFTA Film and Drama Awards programme |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 |publisher=TV3 |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2015}}</ref>\n*22 May \u2013 UTV Ireland airs the second Pride of Ireland Awards, the ceremony having been held at Dublin's [[Mansion House, Dublin|Mansion House]] three days earlier.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://utv.ie/Entertainment/2015/05/19/Pride-of-Ireland-award-winners-announced-37559 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304045302/http://utv.ie/Entertainment/2015/05/19/Pride-of-Ireland-award-winners-announced-37559 |url-status=dead |archive-date=4 March 2016 |title=Pride of Ireland award winners announced |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=19 May 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2015 }}</ref>\n*22 May \u2013 Ireland's national airline, [[Aer Lingus]] launches a new \u20ac2m television advertising campaign that aims to modernise its image.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sorcha |last=Corcoran |url=http://www.businessandleadership.com/marketing/item/50722-aer-lingus-invests-2m-in |title=Aer Lingus invests \u20ac2m in 'smart' TV ad campaign \u2013 Marketing \u2013 Marketing &#124; Ireland's online business and management news service |publisher=Distilled Media |work=Business and Leadership |date=22 May 2015 |accessdate=23 May 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150526043657/http://businessandleadership.com/marketing/item/50722-aer-lingus-invests-2m-in/ |archivedate=26 May 2015 }}</ref>\n*23 May \u2013 Irish voters back a [[Thirty-fourth Amendment of the Constitution (Marriage Equality) Bill 2015|constitutional amendment]] allowing [[same-sex marriage in the Republic of Ireland|same-sex marriage]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/vote2015/2015/0523/703205-referendum-byelection/ |title=Ireland says Yes to same-sex marriage |work=RT\u00c9 News |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=23 May 2015 |accessdate=23 May 2015}}</ref> [[Vincent Browne]] presents TV3's coverage of the results of the previous day's marriage referendum in a special programme, ''Vincent Browne Live from the George'', broadcast from Dublin's popular gay nightclub, [[The George, Dublin|The George]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Freya |last=Drohan |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/vincent-browne-to-host-coverage-of-marriage-referendum-results-live-from-the-george-31241229.html |title=Vincent Browne to host coverage of Marriage Referendum results live from The George |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/referendum/tv3s-vincent-browne-says-marref-result-is-fantastic-and-sings-ole-ole-ole-in-the-george-31248013.html |title=TV3's Vincent Browne says #MarRef result 'is fantastic' and sings Ole Ole Ole in The George |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=23 May 2015 |accessdate=23 May 2015}}</ref> UTV Ireland provides live updates throughout the day, with a special edition of ''[[Ireland Live]]'' at 5.30pm.<ref name=\"UTV-2015-05-08\"/> During RT\u00c9's coverage of proceedings, Senator [[Katherine Zappone]] proposes to her partner, [[Ann Louise Gilligan]] live on air.<ref>{{cite news|first=Clare |last=Cullen |first2=Kathryn |last2=Hayes |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/referendum/theres-nothing-like-an-irish-wedding-senator-katherine-zappone-proposes-live-on-television-31247440.html |title='There's nothing like an Irish wedding' \u2013 Senator Katherine Zappone proposes live on television |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=23 May 2015 |accessdate=23 May 2015}}</ref> President [[Michael D. Higgins]] signs the Marriage Equality Bill into law in August.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2015/0829/724398-marriage-equality-bill/ |title=President signs marriage equality bill |work=RT\u00c9 News |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=29 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*23 May \u2013 ''The Voice of Ireland'' presenter [[Eoghan McDermott]] backtracks from a tweet he sent out shortly after 10.00pm the previous evening protesting at RT\u00c9's marriage referendum gagging order. McDermott says that he posted the tweet, which included the words \"Fuck you RT\u00c9\" because he was in a \"heightened emotional state\".<ref>{{cite news|first=Valerie |last=Loftus |url=http://www.thejournal.ie/eoghan-mcdermott-backtracked-rant-rte-referendum-2120351-May2015/ |title=Eoghan McDermott has backtracked on his rant about RT\u00c9's referendum gag order |publisher=Distilled Media |work=Thejournal.ie |date=23 May 2015 |accessdate=23 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Daniel |last=McDonald |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/referendum/rte-star-eoghan-mcdermott-deletes-f-you-rte-marriage-referendum-post-31247722.html |title=RTE star Eoghan McDermott deletes 'F*** you RTE' Marriage Referendum post |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=23 May 2015 |accessdate=23 May 2015}}</ref>\n*23 May \u2013 Sweden's [[M\u00e5ns Zelmerl\u00f6w]] wins the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2015|2015 Eurovision Song Contest]] with \"[[Heroes (M\u00e5ns Zelmerl\u00f6w song)|Heroes]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2015/0524/703347-sweden/ |title=Sweden Wins Eurovision Song Contest |work=RT\u00c9 News |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=24 May 2015 |accessdate=24 May 2015}}</ref>\n*24 May \u2013 Gaelic football pundit [[Joe Brolly]] is forced to make an on-air apology during RT\u00c9's ''[[The Sunday Game]]'' after describing the tactics of a team as being ugly, and comparable with the looks of RT\u00c9 colleague [[Marty Morrissey]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/news/gaa-pundit-joe-brolly-apologises-over-ugly-jibe-at-rte-colleague-31249789.html |title=GAA pundit Joe Brolly apologises over 'ugly' jibe at RTE colleague |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=Belfast Telegraph |date=25 May 2015 |accessdate=25 May 2015}}</ref>\n*25 May \u2013 [[UTV (TV channel)|UTV]] airs Pat Kenny's interview with Mickey Harte.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.u.tv/Entertainment/2015/05/14/UTV-to-broadcast-Mickey-Harte-interview-37231 |title=UTV to broadcast Mickey Harte interview |work=UTV Ireland |publisher=UTV |date=14 May 2015 |accessdate=20 May 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528223733/http://www.u.tv/Entertainment/2015/05/14/UTV-to-broadcast-Mickey-Harte-interview-37231 |archivedate=28 May 2015 }}</ref> The third edition of ''Pat Kenny in the Round'' to air on UTV Ireland features an interview with singer [[Lulu (singer)|Lulu]], and draws an audience of 95,000. The programme is aired against RT\u00c9's ''[[Crimecall]]'', which is watched by 365,000 viewers.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/pat-kenny-in-the-round-bounces-back-with-lulu-but-is-trounced-by-crimecall-in-ratings-31254417.html |title='Pat Kenny In the Round' bounces back with Lulu but is trounced by 'Crimecall' in ratings |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=26 May 2015 |accessdate=28 May 2015}}</ref>\n*27 May \u2013 [[Ryle Nugent]], RT\u00c9's Group Head of Sport, issues a statement saying that he has spoken to Joe Brolly about \"his ill-conceived attempt at humour [which was] inappropriate and extremely hurtful and had no place\" in ''The Sunday Game''. Nugent says that the matter is now closed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/2015/0527/704188-brolly/ |title=Brolly apologises for Sunday Game comments |work=RT\u00c9 Sport |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=27 May 2015 |accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Declan |last=Whooley |url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/gaelic-football/rte-tell-joe-brolly-similar-comments-wont-be-tolerated-after-marty-morrissey-ugly-jibe-31258445.html |title=RTE tell Joe Brolly 'similar comments won't be tolerated' after Marty Morrissey 'ugly' jibe |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=27 May 2015 |accessdate=28 May 2015}}</ref>\n*28 May \u2013 A statement made to the D\u00e1il by Independent TD [[Catherine Murphy (politician)|Catherine Murphy]] concerning the relationship between media owner Denis O'Brien and IBRC cannot be broadcast by Irish media because of the present injunction against RT\u00c9. Murphy was allowed to speak on the matter because of the law of [[Parliamentary privilege]] that allows parliamentarians to speak on issues without threat of legal action, and the speech is broadcast by [[Oireachtas TV]], which airs proceedings from the [[Oireachtas]]. In the wake of the incident, RT\u00c9 announces that it will seek High Court permission to report the contents of Murphy's statement.<ref>{{cite news|first=Roy |last=Greenslade |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/greenslade/2015/may/29/irelands-media-silenced-over-mps-speech-about-denis-obrien?CMP=ema_546 |title=Ireland's media silenced over MP's speech about Denis O'Brien |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=29 May 2015 |accessdate=31 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Fiachra |last=\u00d3 Cionnaith |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/ireland/rte-to-seek-court-permission-to-report-dail-claims-333749.html |title=RTE to seek court permission to report Dail claims |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=30 May 2015 |accessdate=31 May 2015}}</ref>\n*30 May \u2013 RT\u00c9 announces plans for a \u20ac20,000 revamp of its daily [[The Angelus (television programme)|Angelus]] slot, and will invite film makers to suggest new ideas for the 6.00pm broadcast.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.herald.ie/news/rte-is-set-to-spend-20000-revamping-its-daily-angelus-broadcast-31265396.html |title=RTE is set to spend \u20ac20,000 revamping its daily Angelus broadcast |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Evening Herald |date=30 May 2015 |accessdate=27 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===June===\n*1 June \u2013 Having taken over the broadcast rights from RT\u00c9, TV3 airs the 2015 Irish Film and Television Awards ceremony, which took place on 24 May. The ceremony is watched by an audience of 121,100, compared to 382,000 in 2014. TV3's coverage of the IFTAs is beaten in the ratings by an interview with [[Shane Filan]] on UTV's ''Pat Kenny in the Round'', which draws a viewership of 143,000.<ref>{{cite news|first=Elaine |last=McCahill |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/ifta-show-loses-a-quarter-of-million-viewers-on-tv3-31274754.html |title=IFTA show loses a quarter of million viewers on TV3 |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=3 June 2015 |accessdate=3 June 2015}}</ref>\n*2 June \u2013 Following a legal challenge brought by RT\u00c9, the High Court rules that Ireland's media are free to report Catherine Murphy's D\u00e1il statement about Denis O'Brien and IBRC, and any other comments made under the law of Parliamentary privilege.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/o-brien-rte-high-court-2137331-Jun2015/ |title=Court ruling: Media free to report D\u00e1il comments about Denis O\u2019Brien\u2019s debts |publisher=Distilled Media |work=Thejournal.ie |date=2 June 2015 |accessdate=3 June 2015}}</ref> On 16 June it is reported that O'Brien has launched legal proceedings against the Irish government and the D\u00e1il over Murphy's statement, which O'Brien's lawyers feel was a \"breach of parliamentary privilege\".<ref>{{cite news|first=Lisa |last=O'Carroll |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jun/16/denis-obrien-legal-action-irish-state-banking-remarks |title=Denis O'Brien launches legal action against Irish state over banking remarks |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=16 June 2015 |accessdate=16 June 2015}}</ref>\n*2 June \u2013 UTV Ireland announces ''Daniel and Majella's B&B Road Trip'', a six-part series that will see singer [[Daniel O'Donnell]] and his wife, Majella, visiting [[bed and breakfast]] establishments around Ireland. Filming will begin in July.<ref>{{cite news|first=James |last=Duffin |url=http://utv.ie/Entertainment/2015/06/02/Daniel-ODonnell-to-embark-on-reality-TV-adventure-38306 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150613112119/http://utv.ie/Entertainment/2015/06/02/Daniel-ODonnell-to-embark-on-reality-TV-adventure-38306 |url-status=dead |archive-date=13 June 2015 |title=Daniel O\u2019Donnell to embark on reality TV adventure |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=2 June 2015 |accessdate=3 June 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Evelyn |last=Ring |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/ireland/daniel-and-majella-gear-up-for-bb-road-trip-334266.html |title=Daniel and Majella gear up for B&B road trip |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=3 June 2015 |accessdate=3 June 2015}}</ref> UTV Ireland's announcement of the show, scheduled to air in October, prompts a rush of applications from B&B owning fans eager to have the O'Donnells as their guests.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/utv-ireland-swamped-with-applications-from-bb-landladies-to-have-daniel-odonnell-to-stay-for-new-show-31294729.html |title=UTV Ireland swamped with applications from B&B landladies to have Daniel O'Donnell to stay for new show |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=11 June 2015 |accessdate=11 June 2015}}</ref>\n*3 June \u2013 Justice Donald Binchy, the judge who granted an injunction against RT\u00c9 over its Denis O'Brien story, publishes a redacted summary of his decision. He says the public is not entitled to know \"every detail of the affairs and operation of IBRC\", and because RT\u00c9 had not proved the occurrence of any inappropriate activity by either party. Although the summary is redacted, it is less heavily so because of Catherine Murphy's statement in the D\u00e1il, which put some of the information into the public domain.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/denis-o-brien-rte-2139278-Jun2015/ |title=Here\u2019s why RT\u00c9\u2019s news story about Denis O\u2019Brien was blocked by the courts |publisher=Distilled Media |work=Thejournal.ie |date=3 June 2015 |accessdate=3 June 2015}}</ref>\n*4 June \u2013 TV3's soap ''Red Rock'' airs for the final time before taking a summer break. It will return on 2 September.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/new-tv3-soap-red-rock-off-air-over-the-summer-before-september-return-31206460.html |title=New TV3 soap Red Rock off air over the summer before September return |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=7 May 2015 |accessdate=8 May 2015}}</ref> The season finale ends with a dramatic cliffhanger as Garda Adrijan Kosos (played by Boyko Krastanov) is hit by a car after stopping a motorist. The episode is watched by an average audience of 183,000.<ref>{{cite news|first=Aoife |last=Kelly |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tv3s-red-rock-ends-season-on-a-traumatic-dramatic-high-31279789.html |title=TV3's Red Rock ends season on a traumatic dramatic high |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=5 June 2015 |accessdate=5 June 2015}}</ref>\n*6 June \u2013 To celebrate the 150th anniversary of the birth of [[WB Yeats]] on 13 June, RT\u00c9 announce a series of programmes about the poet across radio and television, including [[Maurice Sweeney]]'s documentary ''WB Yeats: No Country for Old Men'' on RT\u00c9 One on 8 June, and a ''[[Nationwide (Irish TV series)|Nationwide]]'' special from Sligo on 10 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0606/706307-rte-mark-150th-anniversary-of-birth-of-wb-yeats/ |title=RT\u00c9 mark 150th anniversary of birth of WB Yeats |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=6 June 2014 |accessdate=6 June 2015}}</ref>\n*8 June \u2013 Debut of ''Whiskey Business'', a four-part TV3 series charting the Teeling family's attempt to revive the Teeling whiskey brand and establish Ireland's first new whiskey distillery in more than a century.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/tv-news/167676/TV3s-Whiskey-Business-documents-the-journey-of-Irelands-first-new-distillery-in-125-years |title=TV3\u2019s \u2018Whiskey Business\u2019 documents the journey of Ireland\u2019s first new distillery in 125 years |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 |publisher=TV3 |date=22 May 2015 |accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/tv-news/168814/Whiskey-Business-premieres-on-TV3-this-Monday |title=Whiskey Business\u2019 premieres on TV3 this Monday |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 |publisher=TV3 |date=4 June 2015 |accessdate=4 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/first-look-whiskey-business-on-tv3-follows-the-teeling-brothers-as-they-open-irelands-newest-distillery-31277708.html |title=First Look: \u2018Whiskey Business\u2019 on TV3 follows the Teeling brothers as they open Ireland\u2019s newest distillery |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper= |date=4 June 2015 |accessdate=4 June 2015}}</ref>\n*8 June \u2013 Daniel and Majella O'Donnell are guests on the final edition of ''Pat Kenny in the Round'' to air before the summer.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.meathchronicle.ie/entertainment/roundup/articles/2015/06/08/4038148-daniel-and-majella-in-the-round-tonight/ |title=Meath Chronicle \u2013 Daniel and Majella 'In the Round' tonight |publisher= |ne