42 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805222911/http://utv.ie/News/2015/07/02/Clerys-special-on-UTV-Ireland-this-Friday-40242 |url-status=dead |archive-date=5 August 2015 |title=Clerys special on UTV Ireland this Friday |publisher=UTV |work=UTV Ireland |date=2 July 2015 |accessdate=5 July 2015 }}</ref>\n*4 July \u2013 Amid mounting speculation that ''Prime Time'' presenter [[Miriam O'Callaghan (media personality)|Miriam O'Callaghan]] could run for the [[President of Ireland|Irish Presidency]] in [[2018 Irish presidential election|2018]], the  ''Irish Independent'' reports that bosses at RT\u00c9 are under pressure to reveal whether they have held discussions with the broadcaster about the \"potential conflict of interest\" such a move would create.<ref>{{cite news|first=John |last=Downing |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/rt-in-firing-line-over-miriam-ocallaghans-ambitions-for-presidency-31351224.html |title=RT\u00c9 in firing line over Miriam O'Callaghan's 'ambitions for Presidency' |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=4 July 2015 |accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref> RT\u00c9 subsequently says that it has procedures in place to avoid a conflict of interest if such an instance were to arise.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/rte-to-ensure-no-conflict-of-interest-if-miriam-ocallaghan-runs-for-aras-31363592.html |title=RTE to ensure \u2018no conflict of interest\u2019 if Miriam O'Callaghan runs for Aras |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Evening Herald |date=9 July 2015 |accessdate=9 July 2015 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*9 July \u2013 Emma Murphy, a 26-year-old mother from Dublin whose online video in which she spoke about suffering domestic abuse at the hands of her partner went viral within hours of being posted, gives her first television interview to [[Elaine Crowley (presenter)|Elaine Crowley]] on TV