-to-air sub-licensing aspect of the deal. The IOC stipulates in the agreement, which runs from 2018 to 2024, that at least 200 hours of Olympics content should be made available free-to-air in each country.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cummins |first=Mark |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/other-sports/tv3-ponder-challenging-rteacute-for-rights-to-broadcast-olympic-games-346147.html |title=TV3 ponder challenging RTE for rights to broadcast Olympic Games |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=4 August 2015 |accessdate=8 September 2015}}</ref>\n*6 August \u2013 TV3's ''[[Midday (Irish TV series)|Midday]]'' wins praise from its viewers after broadcaster [[Dil Wickremasinghe]] is seen breastfeeding her son live on air.<ref>{{cite news|first=Ciara |last=Flaherty |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/examviral/real-life/broadcaster-praised-after-breastfeeding-live-on-tv3s-midday-346713.html |title=Broadcaster praised after breastfeeding live on TV3's Midday |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=6 August 2015 |accessdate=8 September 2015}}</ref>\n*13 August \u2013 RT\u00c9 One unveils its autumn schedule, which includes 53 new programmes covering documentaries, drama and entertainment. The line-up will see eleven hours of new drama for Sunday nights, including ''[[Clean Break (TV series)|Clean Break]]'', a four-part series written by [[Billy Roche]], and ''Rebellion'', a drama set against the backdrop of the [[Easter Uprising]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288524&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=RT\u00c9 One announces over 50 new titles for new season |work=The Irish Film and Television Network |publisher= |date=13 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*17 August \u2013 RT\u00c9's Comedy, Talent Development and Music department invite proposals for new material to air in peak-time slots on RT\u00c9 One and RT\u00c92 for late autu