0-as-new-tv-channel-costs-mount |title=UTV's profits fall 90% as new TV channel costs mount |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=28 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*28 August \u2013 Launch of the weekend version of TV3's ''[[Ireland AM]]''. ''Saturday AM'' is presented by [[Anna Daly]] and [[Simon Delaney]], while ''Sunday AM'' sees Daly co-presenting alongside [[Ivan Yates]].<ref>{{cite news|first=John |last=Meagher |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/lifestyle/artsfilmtv/filmandtv/anna-daly-fronts-tv3s-new-weekend-morning-showsaturday-am-and-sunday-am-350839.html |title=Anna Daly fronts TV3's new weekend morning show Saturday AM and Sunday AM |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=29 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0804/719086-tv3s-anna-daly-not-under-pressure-to-glam/ |title=No pressure on Anna Daly to look glamorous |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=4 August 2015 |accessdate=8 September 2015}}</ref>\n*28 August \u2013 RT\u00c9 confirms that [[Una Foden]], [[Rachel Stevens]], [[Bressie]] and [[Kian Egan]] will all return as coaches on the [[The Voice of Ireland (series 5)|fifth series]] of ''[[The Voice of Ireland]]'' in January 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2015/0828/724245-judges-set-to-return-for-voice-of-ireland/ |title=All four judges to return for Voice of Ireland |work=RT\u00c9 Ten |publisher=RT\u00c9 |date=28 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*28 August \u2013 [[UPC Ireland]] announces plans to rebrand as Virgin Media Ireland.<ref>{{cite news|first=Adrian |last=Weckler |url=http://www.independent.ie/business/technology/news/upc-to-be-rebranded-as-virgin-media-in-ireland-31485095.html |title=UPC to be rebranded as Virgin Media in Ireland |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=28 August 2015 |accessdate=18 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===September===\n*2 September \u2013 TV3 unveils its autumn schedule, which includes coverage of the [[2015 Rugby World Cup]]. In a subsequent interview with the ''[[The Herald (Ireland)|Evening Herald]]'', Lynda McQuaid, the channel's director of content, reveals that TV3 have been working with US broadcaster [[NBC]] to produce shows for the international market.<ref>{{cite news|first=Sharon |last=McGowan |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/tv3-to-go-global-as-they-work-with-us-network-nbc-on-creating-new-content-31498843.html |title=TV3 to go global as they work with US network NBC on creating new content |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=3 September 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*2 September \u2013 Unveiling their autumn schedule, TV3 announce that it has signed Brian and Pippa Ormond as presenters. The announcement comes a day after Ormonde inadvertently revealed to RT\u00c9 that he will present a new game show for TV3.<ref>{{cite news|last=De Burca |first=Demelza |url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/showbiz/irish-showbiz/tv3-sign-brian-ormond-wife-6371646 |title=TV3 sign Brian Ormond and wife Pippa in surprise double deal in move that will shock RTE |newspaper=Irish Mirror |publisher=Trinity Mirror |date=3 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref> Among the programming in the broadcaster's forthcoming schedule are two documentary series about the murders of [[Sophie Toscan du Plantier]] and Karen Buckley.<ref>{{cite news|first=Evelyn |last=Ring |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/ireland/tv3-to-air-documentaries-on-du-plantier-and-karen-buckley-murders-351671.html |title=TV3 to air documentaries on du Plantier and Karen Buckley murders |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=3 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*2 September \u2013 TV3 airs ''Marilyn Monroe: The Missing Evidence'', a one-off documentary looking at some of the conspiracy theories surrounding the [[death of Marilyn Monroe]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/entertainment-news/176978/TV3-airs-special-uncovering-new-information--about-Marilyn-Monroes-death |title=TV3 airs special uncovering new information about Marilyn Monroe\u2019s death |work=TV3 Xpos\u00e9 |publisher=TV3 |date=31 August 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*2 September \u2013 TV3 reveals that it has signed former [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] footballer [[Graeme Souness]] to join their Champions League analysis team.<ref>{{cite news|first=Larry |last=Ryan |url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/soccer/tv3-snap-up-one-of-rtes-most-popular-pundits-for-champions-league-campaign-351613.html |title=TV3 snap up one of RTE's most popular pundits for Champions League campaign |publisher=Landmark Media Investments |newspaper=The Irish Examiner |date=2 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*4 September \u2013 Sky and RT\u00c9 announce the signing of an agreement that will make more of RT\u00c9's content available on Sky's platform. It will also enable the addition of [[RT\u00c9 One + 1]] and [[RT\u00c9 News Now]] to the Sky lineup.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/business/world/sky-and-rte-sign-channelcontent-partnership-31502572.html |title=Sky and RTE sign channel/content partnership |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=3 September 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*6 September \u2013 UTV Ireland confirms that it has axed Pat Kenny's chat show ''In the Round'', which was due to return for a second run in Autumn 2015, because of poor ratings. That series will no longer go ahead.<ref>{{cite news|first=Niamh |last=Horan |url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/republic-of-ireland/utv-ireland-axe-pat-kenny-chat-show-31505719.html |title=UTV Ireland axe Pat Kenny chat show |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=Belfast Telegraph |date=6 September 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2015 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*7 September \u2013 Recording of a debate for TV3's ''[[Tonight with Vincent Browne]]'' is halted when Garda\u00ed are called to the venue to deal with jeering audience members and anti-water charge protestors. It is also alleged that a male member of the audience threatened a woman during the event, being held [[Clontarf Castle]] in [[Dublin Bay North (D\u00e1il constituency)|Dublin Bay North]] because she applauded equality minister [[Aodh\u00e1n \u00d3 R\u00edord\u00e1in]]. TV3 subsequently announces that the chaotic scenes will be edited out of the debate, which is broadcast two days later.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/vincent-browne-peoples-debate-clontarf-castle-2317802-Sep2015/ |title=Garda\u00ed called after Vincent Browne debate descends into mayhem |publisher=Thejournal.ie |date=8 December 2015 |accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=David |last=Kearns |url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/tv3-to-edit-out-chaotic-scenes-after-vincent-browne-debate-ends-in-threats-31514827.html |title=TV3 to edit out 'chaotic scenes' after Vincent Browne debate ends in threats |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=9 September 2015 |accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref>\n*10 September \u2013 [[Irish Film and Television Awards|IFTA]] confirms a three-year deal with Irish retailer [[Gala (supermarket)|Gala]] to sponsor the [[Irish Film and Television Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288599&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=IFTA announce Gala as the Headline Sponsor for the annual Television Awards |publisher=The Irish Film & Television Network |date=10 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*11 September \u2013 Official launch of the IFTA Gala Television Awards, which will take place on 22 October at Dublin's Double Tree Hotel.<ref>{{cite news|first=Se\u00e1n |last=Brosnan |url=http://www.iftn.ie/rep_bodies/repbodiesnews/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4288606&tpl=archnews&force=1 |title=IFTA Gala Television Awards is launched |publisher=The Irish Film & Television Network |date=11 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*14 September \u2013 UTV Ireland launches a new on-screen branding featuring people such as farmers, tattoo artists and designers with the strapline \u201cYOU TV\u201d. UTV hopes the new look will \"reinvigorate\" the brand.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/utv-new-look-rebrand-2328469-Sep2015/ |title=Nine months in, UTV Ireland launches \u2018new look\u2019 to connect with their audience |publisher=Thejournal.ie |date=13 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*18 September \u2013 UTV launches a new version of its [[UTV Player]], allowing viewers to stream live content for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.u.tv/Press/2015/09/18/UTV-launches-free-live-streaming-ahead-of-the-Rugby-World-Cup-45238 |title=UTV launches free live streaming ahead of the Rugby World Cup |publisher=UTV |work=UTV |date=18 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304081600/http://www.u.tv/Press/2015/09/18/UTV-launches-free-live-streaming-ahead-of-the-Rugby-World-Cup-45238 |archivedate=4 March 2016 }}</ref>\n*20 September \u2013 The final series of ''[[Downton Abbey]]'' debuts on ITV, but is absent from the schedules of UTV Ireland. Instead the series makes its Irish television debut two days later on TV3.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertainment.ie/tv/news/Yes-Downton-will-NOT-be-on-UTV-Ireland-No-weve-no-idea-why-that-is/370475.htm |title=TV News &#124; Yes, Downton will NOT be on UTV Ireland. No, we've no idea why that is. |publisher=Entertainment.ie |date=20 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n*26 September \u2013 UTV Ireland presenter [[Jenny Buckley]] tells the ''[[Irish Daily Mirror]]'' that the channel plans to expand her entertainment show ''The Pulse'' to a 30-minute slot by the end of the year.<ref>{{cite news|last=De-Burca |first=Demelza |url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/whats-on/film-and-tv/jenny-buckley-set-go-head-6517292 |title=Jenny Buckley set to go head-to-head with Xpose as The Pulse is extended to 30 minutes |newspaper=Irish Daily Mirror |publisher=Trinity Mirror |date=26 September 2015 |accessdate=6 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Caitlin |last=McBride |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/television/tv-news/let-the-ratings-battle-begin-utvs-the-pulse-to-go-head-to-head-with-tv3s-xpose-31559900.html |title=Let the ratings battle begin: UTV's The Pulse to go head to head with TV3's Xpose |publisher=Independent News and Media |newspaper=The Irish Independent |date=26 September 2015 |accessdate=6 October 2015}}</ref>\n*30 September \u2013 The Independent Broadcasters of Ireland, the body representing 34 of Ireland's independent radio stations calls for all public service broadcasting to be funded through the television licence fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/independent-broadcasters-of-ireland-calls-for-television-licence-fee-overhaul-698363.html |title=Independent Broadcasters of Ireland calls for television licence fee overhaul |publisher=BreakingNews.ie |date=30 September 2015 |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n===October===\n*4 October \u2013 [[Ireland national rugby union team|Ireland]]'s final group stage [[2015 Rugby World Cup|Rugby World Cup]] match against [[Italy national rugby union team|Italy]] draws an audience of 1.38 million. Of those watching the game, an average 956,600 do so on TV3, with figures peaking at 1.18 million, giving the channel its highest ever ratings.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/business/tv3-celebrates-highest-ever-ratings-as-138-million-tune-in-t